{"title_page": "Protests over responses to the 2020 coronavirus pandemic", "text_new": "{{mergefrom|2020 Lansing, Michigan protest|discuss=Talk:Protests over responses to the 2020 coronavirus pandemic#Merge request|date=April 2020}}\n{{Globalize|1=article|2=United States|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{2019-20 coronavirus pandemic sidebar}}\n\nIn the United States in April 2020, protests were organized by [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]-connected groups<ref name=\"Grauniad-Right\">{{Cite news|last=Wilson|first=Jason|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/17/far-right-coronavirus-protests-restrictions|title=The rightwing groups behind wave of protests against Covid-19 restrictions|date=2020-04-17|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-18|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> in several locations across the United States.<ref>{{cite news|last=Andone|first=Dakin|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/16/us/protests-coronavirus-stay-home-orders/index.html|title=Protests Are Popping Up Across the US over Stay-at-Home Restrictions|date=April 17, 2020|publisher=CNN}}</ref> The protests opposed the measures state governments were taking to combat the  [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|coronavirus pandemic]], such as business closures and stay-at-home orders, and demanded that their state be \"re-opened\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/04/18/837776218/across-america-frustrated-protesters-rally-to-reopen-the-economy|title=Across America, Frustrated Protesters Rally To Reopen The Economy|last=Siegler|first=Kirk|date=April 18, 2020|work=NPR|accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>  The protests made international news.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52330531|title=Coronavirus: Anti-Lockdown Protests Grow Across US|date=April 17, 2020|access-date=April 17, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417172715/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52330531|archive-date=April 17, 2020|publisher=BBC News|department=US & Canada}}</ref><ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/21/us/politics/coronavirus-protests-trump.html</ref>\n\n==Background==\nOne of the first protests was in [[Michigan]]. It was organized via a Facebook group called Operation Gridlock, which was created by the Michigan Freedom Fund and the Michigan Conservative Coalition. A spokesman for the Michigan Conservative Coalition encouraged groups in other states to copy the Operation Gridlock wording and templates. Protesters in numerous other states said they were inspired by Michigan, and they used Michigan\u2019s material on their own websites, [[Facebook]] groups, and [[Reddit]] pages to promote their protests. Michigan Governor [[Gretchen Whitmer]] called attention to the fact that the Michigan Freedom Fund is funded in part by the DeVos family, but a spokesman said the family had nothing to do with the protests.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/salvadorhernandez/coronavirus-quarantine-protests-facebook-groups|title=This Is How A Group Linked To Betsy DeVos Is Organizing Protests To End Social Distancing, Now With Trump's Support|website=BuzzFeed News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> \n\nThe Trump campaign declined to answer whether it was directly involved with organizing the protest in Michigan but key organizers who did identify themselves were Meshawn Maddock, the wife of Republican Rep. [[Matt Maddock]] who is on the national advisory board for [[Women for Trump]], and Marian Sheridan who serves as a vice chair on the [[Michigan Republican Party]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-trump-protests-idUSKCN2233ES|title=How Trump allies have organized and promoted anti-lockdown protests|date=2020-04-22|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-23|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bridgemi.com/michigan-government/meet-trump-loving-group-behind-protest-gov-whitmers-stay-home-order|title=Meet the Trump-loving group behind protest of Gov. Whitmer\u2019s stay-home order|date=2020-04-22|website=www.bridgemi.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\nProtesters opposed the shelter-in-place orders in their states for various reasons. Many said they want businesses reopened so they can go back to work. Many others displayed pro-Trump banners, signs, and MAGA hats.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2020/04/16/michigan-whitmer-conservatives-protest/|title=Chanting \u2018lock her up,\u2019 Michigan protesters waving Trump flags mass against Gov. Gretchen Whitmer\u2019s coronavirus restrictions|last=Flynn|first=Meagan|date=April 16, 2020|work=The Washington Post|accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref> Still others insisted the lockdowns were a violation of their constitutional rights. One militia leader told a reporter, \"Re-open my state or we will re-open it ourselves.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52359100|title=Coronavirus lockdown protest: What's behind the US demonstrations?|date=April 21, 2020|work=BBC News|accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe reopen protests have generally been small, with protestor numbers in the low hundreds. Protesters included mainstream Republicans,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2020/04/trump-supporters-protest-coronavirus-orders|title=Trump Supporters Are Staging Armed Protests to Stick It to Coronavirus|last=Ecarma|first=Caleb|website=Vanity Fair}}</ref> but also far-right groups including [[Proud Boys]] and armed militia movements.<ref name=\"Grauniad-Right\" /> A large number of \"[[Vaccine hesitancy|anti-vax]]\" advocates have also been in attendance, sometimes accompanied by their children. Ben, Chris and Aaron Dorr, three guns-rights activist brothers from [[Northfield, Minnesota]], are the organizers of protests in several midwestern states.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bringmethenews.com/minnesota-news/washington-post-links-minnesota-gun-group-to-anti-quarantine-protests|title=WaPo reveals Minnesota gun group link to anti-quarantine protests|last=Uren|first=Adam|website=Bring Me The News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== Protests by U.S. state ==\n\n=== California ===\nOn April 17, a group of more than 100 protested against the stay-at-home rules in [[Huntington Beach, California|Huntington Beach]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-04-17/protesters-california-stay-at-home-coronavirus|title=\u2018Live Free or Die\u2019: Protesters march against California stay-at-home rules in Huntington Beach|date=April 17, 2020|website=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\n\nOn April 18, several hundred people protested in [[Downtown San Diego]], saying they want businesses and beaches reopened.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.kpbs.org/news/2020/apr/18/protesters-us-san-diego-coronavirus-stay-at-home/|title=Protesters Decry Coronavirus Stat-At-Home Orders Across The US, Including San Diego|website=KPBS Public Media|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cbs8.com/article/news/local/freedom-rally/509-cffea06c-d18e-4a45-8e8a-517961c6ae5b|title=San Diego groups protest government-imposed shutdown orders|website=KFMB|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcsandiego.com/news/local/san-diegans-against-stay-at-home-order-protest-in-downtown/2308634/|title=Protestors Against Stay-at-Home Order Rally in Downtown|website=NBC 7 San Diego|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>. Another protest occurred April 19 in [[Encinitas, California|Encinitas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbs8.com/article/news/local/encinitas-protest-beach-losures/509-e3386f42-e860-43ca-a9e2-48394b718511|title=Encinitas group gathers to protest the closure of public spaces in North County San Diego|website=KFMB|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nOn April 20, hundreds of protesters marched or drove around the [[California State Capitol]] in [[Sacramento, California|Sacramento]]. The rally was organized by the Freedom Angels, a group best known for its opposition to mandatory vaccination.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/politics/article/Protesters-besiege-Capitol-in-Sacramento-they-15214025.php|title=Protesters besiege Capitol in Sacramento - they want coronavirus restrictions lifted|date=2020-04-21|website=SFChronicle.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n=== Colorado ===\nA Facebook event was created for a gathering called \"Operation Gridlock Denver\" for April 19, with more than 550 people stating they were going to the event. The operation plan was to \"drive to the capitol in Denver and gridlock the roads in protest to the mandatory lockdowns and violation of constitutional rights...\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://denverite.com/2020/04/17/yes-denver-officials-are-aware-of-that-gridlock-protest-on-sunday-thats-breaking-stay-at-home-orders/|title=Yes, Denver officials are aware of that \"gridlock\" protest on Sunday that's breaking stay-at-home orders|last=Hernandez|first=Esteban|date=2020-04-17|website=Denverite|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nFootage from the counter-protest went viral after nurses silently stood in front of cars participating in the protest Operation Gridlock, while wearing their scrubs and [[N95 mask|N95 face masks]]. One nurse who participated in the counter-protest stated the protest felt like \"a slap in the face to medical workers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/health-care-workers-took-stand-against-protestors-opposing-coronavirus-lockdown-n1187711|title=Health care workers stand against protesters opposing coronavirus lockdown in Colorado|last=Kesslen|first=Ben|date=April 20, 2020|website=NBC News|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> The nurses stood in the crosswalk during red lights as a reminder to why the shut down measures were needed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/photos-purportedly-show-coronavirus-protest-standoff|title=Coronavirus standoff: Photos purportedly show Colorado health care workers at odds with anti-lockdown protesters|last=Norman|first=Greg|date=2020-04-20|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n=== Idaho ===\nSeveral hundred protesters assembled at the [[Idaho State Capitol]] buildiing in Boise under the slogan \"Disobey Idaho\" on April 17. The  protest was organized byby three conservative groups \u2014 the \"Idaho Freedom Foundation\", \"Idaho Second Amendment Alliance\" and \"Health Freedom Idaho\" and emceed by [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] [[Idaho Legislature|state representative]] [[Tammy Nichols]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bustillo|first=Ximena|url=https://www.idahostatesman.com/news/coronavirus/article242092321.html|title=Hundreds rally at Idaho Capitol to protest Gov. Little\u2019s stay-home order|date=Mar 17, 2020|work=Idaho Statesman|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/hundreds-defy-idahos-stay-at-home-order-at-capitol-protest/2020/04/17/04cf4480-80fa-11ea-84c2-0792d8591911_story.html|title=Hundreds defy Idaho\u2019s stay-at-home order at Capitol protest|last=AP|first=Rebecca Boone {{!}}|website=Washington Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n===Indiana===\nOn Saturday, April 18, approximately 250<ref name=\"IndyStar\">{{cite news |last1=Pak-Harvey |first1=Amelia |title=Protesters rally outside Governor's Residence to say Holcomb's orders go too far |url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/local/marion-county/2020/04/18/indiana-coronavirus-protesters-say-gov-holcombs-orders-go-too-far/5148983002/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Indianapolis Star |agency=Ganett |date=18 April 2020}}</ref> people gathered  in front of the Governor's Mansion in [[Indianapolis]] to protest Governor [[Eric Holcomb]]'s stay at home order.  The protesters did not follow social distancing guidelines, although some wore [[Face masks during the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|face masks]].  The protesters called for the Governor to appear and explain himself, and said they were willing to be arrested if necessary.<ref name=\"Indiana\">{{cite news |last1=Staff Report |title=Dozens protest Indiana \u2018stay at home\u2019 order outside governor\u2019s mansion |url=https://www.wishtv.com/news/indiana-news/dozens-protest-indiana-stay-at-home-order-outside-governors-mansion/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=WISH TV |date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Kentucky===\nDozens of people gathered on the lawn of the state capitol in [[Frankfort, Kentucky|Frankfort]] in the afternoon of Wednesday, April 15, 2020 to protest Governor [[Andy Beshear]]'s anti-coronavirus measures. They could also be heard inside the capitol building. Throughout Governor Beshea 's one-hour press briefing, the protesters chanted continuously and occasionally blew a horn. The principal demand was that businesses in the State be reopened.<ref name=\"kara_b_and_paul_e_15\">{{cite news|last1=Berg|first1=Kara|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/04/15/lansing-capitol-protest-michigan-stay-home-order/5139472002/|title=Thousands Converge to Protest Michigan Governor's Stay-Home Order in 'Operation Gridlock'|date=April 15, 2020|work=USA Today|access-date=April 15, 2020|last2=Egan|first2=Paul|last-author-amp=yes}}</ref>\n\n===Michigan===\n{{Main|2020 Lansing, Michigan protest}}\nThousands of people protested, mainly in cars, in a protest they called [[2020 Lansing, Michigan protest|\"Operation Gridlock\"]] in the vicinity of the [[Michigan State Capitol]] in [[Lansing, Michigan]], on April 15, 2020.<ref name=\"kara_b_and_paul_e_15\" /> Protesters had arrived by 9:00 am and the protest was ongoing, although shrinking, at 4:30 pm.<ref name=\"heatherwalk_15\">{{cite news|last=Walker|first=Heather|url=https://www.upmatters.com/news/protesters-in-opposition-of-stay-home-order-gather-at-michigan-capitol/|title='Free MI': Stay-home order protesters gather at Capitol|date=April 15, 2020|work=UP Matters|access-date=April 17, 2020|publisher=[[WJMN-TV]]|location=Marquette, Michigan}}</ref>\n\n===North Carolina===\nIn [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh]], people protested outside the capitol building on Tuesday, April 14, 2020. Some were arrested.<ref name=\"gabriel_sanch_15\">{{cite news|last=Sanchez|first=Gabriel H.|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/gabrielsanchez/huge-crowds-protest-coronavirus-trump-coronavirus-pandemic|title=These Pictures Show Huge Crowds Protesting Against Coronavirus Lockdowns at State Capitols|date=April 16, 2020|work=Buzzfeed News|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Ohio===\n[[File:Columbus coronavirus protests at the Ohio Statehouse, 2020-04-18j.jpg|thumb|An anti-lockdown protest at the [[Ohio Statehouse]], April 18, 2020]]\n\nProtests began in Ohio on April 9 with about 75 gathering outside of the statehouse and occurred again on the 13th growing to a group of 200-300.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite news|author=Cincinnati CityBeat Staff|url=https://www.clevescene.com/scene-and-heard/archives/2020/04/14/were-not-afraid-of-any-virus-crowds-gathered-outside-of-ohio-statehouse-protesting-coronavirus-shutdowns|title='We're Not Afraid of Any Virus': Crowds Gathered Outside of Ohio Statehouse Protesting Coronavirus Shutdowns|date=April 14, 2020|work=Cleveland Scene|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe following weekend, Protests began on Friday, April 17 with dozens protesting outside the east side of the Statehouse.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dispatch.com/photogallery/OH/20200418/PHOTOGALLERY/418009999/PH/1|title=Photos: Protests over stay-at-home orders at Ohio Statehouse|website=The Columbus Dispatch|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> The next day, April 18, the protests grew to hundreds who came to protest Governor DeWine's stay at home order.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/open/2020/04/hundreds-protest-in-columbus-against-ohio-coronavirus-restrictions.html|title=Hundreds protest in Columbus against Ohio coronavirus restrictions|last=Hancock|first=Laura|last2=clevel|date=2020-04-18|website=cleveland|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20|last3=.com}}</ref><ref name=\":4\" />  Protesters carried signs concerned with the loss of liberties for the sake of safety, as well as signs critical of State officials,<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> and demanded that the State be immediately reopened.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\nThe Governor has said that he will not interfere with the protests, at least provided they adhere to social distancing guidelines.<ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/ohio-governor-protests-are-ok-if-protestors-socially-distance-2020-4|title=Ohio governor says anti-lockdown protests are OK if protestors adhere to social distancing|last=Perrett|first=Connor|website=Business Insider|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>  Photographs from the protests on April 18 indicate that not all of protesters had been.<ref name=\":6\" /> Though, the protests also involved those who stayed in cars.<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n\n===Oregon===\nIn Oregon, dozens of protesters circled the Oregon State Capitol in Salem in their vehicles on April 17, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.registerguard.com/news/20200418/coronavirus-updates-saturday-dozens-protest-oregonrsquos-stay-at-home-order-butte-to-butte-race-canceled|title=Coronavirus updates, Saturday: Dozens protest Oregon's stay-at-home order; Butte to Butte race canceled|first=Staff, news|last=services|website=The Register-Guard}}</ref> 200 people gathered outside City Hall in [[Redmond, Oregon|Redmond]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ktvz.com/news/2020/04/17/protest-planned-in-redmond-against-stay-at-home-order/|title=More than 200 gather in Redmond to protest stay-at-home order|first1=Max|last1=Goldwasser|first2=The Associated|last2=Press|date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bendbulletin.com/coronavirus/redmond-activist-to-protest-oregon-stay-home-order-with-rally/article_ce398714-8040-11ea-83b4-97b0b821091c.html|title=Redmond activist to protest Oregon stay home order with rally|first=GARRETT ANDREWS The|last=Bulletin|website=The Bulletin}}</ref>\n\nThe \"Re-Open Oregon\" rally is planned for May 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koin.com/news/health/coronavirus/open-oregon-rally-arrives-in-salem/|title=\u2018Open Oregon\u2019 rally in Salem: \u2018No light at end of tunnel\u2019|date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portlandmercury.com/blogtown/2020/04/16/28299387/conservative-protestors-plan-reopen-oregon-rally-at-state-capitol|title=Conservative Protestors Plan \"Reopen Oregon\" Rally at State Capitol|first1=Blair Stenvick \u2022|last1=Apr 16|first2=2020 at 11:16|last2=Am|website=Portland Mercury}}</ref>\n\n=== Pennsylvania ===\nOn [[Patriots' Day]], April 20, hundreds of protesters marched on the state capital building during a Monday morning \u201cOperation Gridlock Pennsylvania\u201d event  in [[Harrisburg, Pennsylvania|Harrisburg]].<ref name=\"olson1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/hundreds-of-protesters-line-harrisburg-streets-in-protest-against-stay-at-home-order|title=Hundreds of protesters line Harrisburg streets in rowdy protest against stay-at-home order|last=Olson|first=Tyler|date=2020-04-20|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> The protest was  organized by three groups, \u201cRe-open Pennsylvania,\u201d \u201cEnd the Lockdown Pennsylvania,\u201d and \u201cPennsylvania Against Excessive Quarantine\u201d led in part by an Ohio-based 2nd amendment rights activist named Chris Dorr.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc27.com/news/local/harrisburg/thousands-of-protesters-expected-at-a-reopen-rally/|title=Thousands of protesters expected at a \u2018reopen rally\u2019|date=2020-04-20|website=ABC27|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref name=\"olson1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailyitem.com/news/update-hundreds-gather-at-capitol-in-harrisburg-for-anti-shutdown-rally-calling-to-reopen-pennsylvania/article_7d4f6946-831e-11ea-b61e-3f87f608ab01.html|title=UPDATE Hundreds gather at Capitol in Harrisburg for anti-shutdown rally calling to \u2018reopen\u2019 Pennsylvania|last=PA|first=Cynthia Fernandez of Spotlight|website=The Daily Item|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>  \n\n=== Texas ===\nOn Saturday, April 18, hundreds protested at the statehouse in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]] at a \"You Can't Close America\" rally organized by ''[[InfoWars]]''{{'}} [[Alex Jones]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/alex-jones-coronavirus-lockdown-protest-texas-anthony-fauci-fire-a9472611.html|title=Alex Jones joins protest against coronavirus lockdown orders as crowds chant \u2018Fire Fauci\u2019|date=2020-04-18|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n===Washington===\nIn Washington State, the Kitsap County Republican Party coordinated the event \"Hazardous Liberty! Defend the Constitution!\" in Olympia on April 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://komonews.com/news/coronavirus/protest-against-state-closure-planned-for-tomorrow-in-olympia|title=Protest against state closure planned for tomorrow in Olympia|first=Cole Miller &#124; KOMO|last=News|date=April 18, 2020|website=KOMO}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.king5.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/people-plan-to-gather-in-olympia-sunday-to-protest-gov-inslees-stay-at-home-order/281-d7920d24-f6b8-4b75-b63d-27bd8b605d0b|title=People plan to gather in Olympia Sunday to protest Gov. Inslee\u2019s stay-at-home order|website=KING}}</ref> the Olympia event was attended by over 2,000 people.<ref>\"Demonstrators rally in Olympia against Washington\u2019s coronavirus stay-at-home order\", The Seattle Times, April 20, 2020, page 1</ref>\n\n== Response ==\nOn April 16 President [[Donald Trump]] issued guidelines for how to phase out restrictions, saying that governors would decide how to reopen their own states and suggesting a cautious three-phase approach.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/16/politics/donald-trump-reopening-guidelines-coronavirus/index.html|title=Trump completes reversal, telling govs 'you are going to call your own shots' and distributes new guidelines|date=April 16, 2020|work=CNN|accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref> The next day he reacted to the protests against social restrictions by encouraging the protests, tweeting \"LIBERATE MICHIGAN!\" and \"LIBERATE MINNESOTA!\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/17/us/politics/trump-coronavirus-governors.html|title=Trump Encourages Protest Against Governors Who Have Imposed Virus Restrictions|last1=Shear|first1=Michael D.|last2=Mervosh|first2=Sarah|date=April 17, 2020|work=The New York Times|accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Itkowitz|first=Colby|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2020/04/17/liberate-trump-tweets-support-protesting-against-stay-at-home-orders/|title='Liberate': Trump Tweets Support of Protests Against Stay-at-Home Orders|date=April 17, 2020|work=[[The Washington Post]]|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/17/us/coronavirus-cases-news-update.html|title=Trump Foments Protests Against Governors; Experts Warn of Testing Shortages|date=2020-04-17|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-18|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> [[Jay Inslee|Governor Jay Inslee]] (D-WA) accused the President of \"fomenting domestic rebellion\" with these tweets: \"The president's statements this morning encourage illegal and dangerous acts. He is putting millions of people in danger of contracting [[COVID-19]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/trump-accused-fomenting-rebellion-liberate-tweets-200417223606672.html|title=Trump accused of 'fomenting rebellion' after 'LIBERATE' tweets|website=www.aljazeera.com|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref> On [[This Week (American TV program)|ABC's This Week]] two days later, Inslee said the President's call to ignore his own team's guidelines was \"schizophrenic.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2020/04/19/governors-decry-trump-call-liberate-states-coronavirus-restrictions/5162196002/|title=Governors slam Trump's call to 'liberate' states where protesters object to coronavirus restrictions|last=Cummings|first=William|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nTrump has continued to encourage the protesters' defiance of [[social distancing]] orders by saying  \"They seem very responsible to me.\"<ref>{{Cite news|last=Reuters/AP|first=Source:|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2020/apr/18/they-seem-very-responsible-to-me-trump-defends-anti-lockdown-protesters-video|title='They seem very responsible to me': Trump defends anti-lockdown protesters - video|date=2020-04-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-19|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> [[Stephen Moore (writer)|Stephen Moore]], a right-wing member of his economic council, stoked [[List of incidents of xenophobia and racism related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|racial passions]] by comparing the protesters to [[Rosa Parks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/493484-trump-ally-compares-coronavirus-protesters-to-rosa-parks|title=Trump ally compares coronavirus protesters to Rosa Parks|last=Johnson|first=Martin|date=2020-04-18|website=TheHill|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n[[Facebook]] has started blocking events and messages from anti-quarantine protest groups \"when gatherings do not follow the health parameters established by the government and are therefore unlawful.\" The Governors of [[Phil Murphy|New Jersey]] and [[Pete Ricketts|Nebraska]] have stated that they have not requested that Facebook take the posts down. The company appears to be doing it on their own volition but [[Donald Trump Jr.|Donald Trump, Jr.]] claims they are \"[[colluding]] with state governments to quash [[Freedom of speech|free speech]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/20/facebook-shuts-down-anti-quarantine-protests-at-states-request-196143|title=Republicans attack Facebook as network shuts down anti-lockdown protests|last=Overly|first=Steven|website=POLITICO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on politics]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States}}\n\n[[Category:2020 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States]]\n[[Category:Protests in the United States]]\n[[Category:Protests over responses to the 2020 coronavirus pandemic| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{mergefrom|2020 Lansing, Michigan protest|discuss=Talk:Protests over responses to the 2020 coronavirus pandemic#Merge request|date=April 2020}}\n{{Globalize|1=article|2=United States|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{2019-20 coronavirus pandemic sidebar}}\n\nIn the United States in April 2020, protests were organized by [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]-connected groups<ref name=\"Grauniad-Right\">{{Cite news|last=Wilson|first=Jason|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/17/far-right-coronavirus-protests-restrictions|title=The rightwing groups behind wave of protests against Covid-19 restrictions|date=2020-04-17|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-18|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> in several locations across the United States.<ref>{{cite news|last=Andone|first=Dakin|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/16/us/protests-coronavirus-stay-home-orders/index.html|title=Protests Are Popping Up Across the US over Stay-at-Home Restrictions|date=April 17, 2020|publisher=CNN}}</ref> The protests opposed the measures state governments were taking to combat the  [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|coronavirus pandemic]], such as business closures and stay-at-home orders, and demanded that their state be \"re-opened\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/04/18/837776218/across-america-frustrated-protesters-rally-to-reopen-the-economy|title=Across America, Frustrated Protesters Rally To Reopen The Economy|last=Siegler|first=Kirk|date=April 18, 2020|work=NPR|accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>  The protests made international news.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52330531|title=Coronavirus: Anti-Lockdown Protests Grow Across US|date=April 17, 2020|access-date=April 17, 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417172715/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52330531|archive-date=April 17, 2020|publisher=BBC News|department=US & Canada}}</ref><ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/21/us/politics/coronavirus-protests-trump.html</ref>\n\n==Background==\nOne of the first protests was in [[Michigan]]. It was organized via a Facebook group called Operation Gridlock, which was created by the Michigan Freedom Fund and the Michigan Conservative Coalition. A spokesman for the Michigan Conservative Coalition encouraged groups in other states to copy the Operation Gridlock wording and templates. Protesters in numerous other states said they were inspired by Michigan, and they used Michigan\u2019s material on their own websites, [[Facebook]] groups, and [[Reddit]] pages to promote their protests. Michigan Governor [[Gretchen Whitmer]] called attention to the fact that the Michigan Freedom Fund is funded in part by the DeVos family, but a spokesman said the family had nothing to do with the protests.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/salvadorhernandez/coronavirus-quarantine-protests-facebook-groups|title=This Is How A Group Linked To Betsy DeVos Is Organizing Protests To End Social Distancing, Now With Trump's Support|website=BuzzFeed News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> \n\nThe Trump campaign declined to answer whether it was directly involved with organizing the protest in Michigan but key organizers who did identify themselves were found also to be Meshawn Maddock, the wife of Republican Rep. [[Matt Maddock]] who is on the national advisory board for [[Women for Trump]], and Marian Sheridan who serves as a vice chair on the [[Michigan Republican Party]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-trump-protests-idUSKCN2233ES|title=How Trump allies have organized and promoted anti-lockdown protests|date=2020-04-22|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-23|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bridgemi.com/michigan-government/meet-trump-loving-group-behind-protest-gov-whitmers-stay-home-order|title=Meet the Trump-loving group behind protest of Gov. Whitmer\u2019s stay-home order|date=2020-04-22|website=www.bridgemi.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\nProtesters opposed the shelter-in-place orders in their states for various reasons. Many said they want businesses reopened so they can go back to work. Many others displayed pro-Trump banners, signs, and MAGA hats.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2020/04/16/michigan-whitmer-conservatives-protest/|title=Chanting \u2018lock her up,\u2019 Michigan protesters waving Trump flags mass against Gov. Gretchen Whitmer\u2019s coronavirus restrictions|last=Flynn|first=Meagan|date=April 16, 2020|work=The Washington Post|accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref> Still others insisted the lockdowns were a violation of their constitutional rights. One militia leader told a reporter, \"Re-open my state or we will re-open it ourselves.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52359100|title=Coronavirus lockdown protest: What's behind the US demonstrations?|date=April 21, 2020|work=BBC News|accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe reopen protests have generally been small, with protestor numbers in the low hundreds. Protesters included mainstream Republicans,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2020/04/trump-supporters-protest-coronavirus-orders|title=Trump Supporters Are Staging Armed Protests to Stick It to Coronavirus|last=Ecarma|first=Caleb|website=Vanity Fair}}</ref> but also far-right groups including [[Proud Boys]] and armed militia movements.<ref name=\"Grauniad-Right\" /> A large number of \"[[Vaccine hesitancy|anti-vax]]\" advocates have also been in attendance, sometimes accompanied by their children. Ben, Chris and Aaron Dorr, three guns-rights activist brothers from [[Northfield, Minnesota]], are the organizers of protests in several midwestern states.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bringmethenews.com/minnesota-news/washington-post-links-minnesota-gun-group-to-anti-quarantine-protests|title=WaPo reveals Minnesota gun group link to anti-quarantine protests|last=Uren|first=Adam|website=Bring Me The News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== Protests by U.S. state ==\n\n=== California ===\nOn April 17, a group of more than 100 protested against the stay-at-home rules in [[Huntington Beach, California|Huntington Beach]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-04-17/protesters-california-stay-at-home-coronavirus|title=\u2018Live Free or Die\u2019: Protesters march against California stay-at-home rules in Huntington Beach|date=April 17, 2020|website=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\n\nOn April 18, several hundred people protested in [[Downtown San Diego]], saying they want businesses and beaches reopened.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.kpbs.org/news/2020/apr/18/protesters-us-san-diego-coronavirus-stay-at-home/|title=Protesters Decry Coronavirus Stat-At-Home Orders Across The US, Including San Diego|website=KPBS Public Media|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cbs8.com/article/news/local/freedom-rally/509-cffea06c-d18e-4a45-8e8a-517961c6ae5b|title=San Diego groups protest government-imposed shutdown orders|website=KFMB|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcsandiego.com/news/local/san-diegans-against-stay-at-home-order-protest-in-downtown/2308634/|title=Protestors Against Stay-at-Home Order Rally in Downtown|website=NBC 7 San Diego|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>. Another protest occurred April 19 in [[Encinitas, California|Encinitas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbs8.com/article/news/local/encinitas-protest-beach-losures/509-e3386f42-e860-43ca-a9e2-48394b718511|title=Encinitas group gathers to protest the closure of public spaces in North County San Diego|website=KFMB|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nOn April 20, hundreds of protesters marched or drove around the [[California State Capitol]] in [[Sacramento, California|Sacramento]]. The rally was organized by the Freedom Angels, a group best known for its opposition to mandatory vaccination.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/politics/article/Protesters-besiege-Capitol-in-Sacramento-they-15214025.php|title=Protesters besiege Capitol in Sacramento - they want coronavirus restrictions lifted|date=2020-04-21|website=SFChronicle.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n=== Colorado ===\nA Facebook event was created for a gathering called \"Operation Gridlock Denver\" for April 19, with more than 550 people stating they were going to the event. The operation plan was to \"drive to the capitol in Denver and gridlock the roads in protest to the mandatory lockdowns and violation of constitutional rights...\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://denverite.com/2020/04/17/yes-denver-officials-are-aware-of-that-gridlock-protest-on-sunday-thats-breaking-stay-at-home-orders/|title=Yes, Denver officials are aware of that \"gridlock\" protest on Sunday that's breaking stay-at-home orders|last=Hernandez|first=Esteban|date=2020-04-17|website=Denverite|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nFootage from the counter-protest went viral after nurses silently stood in front of cars participating in the protest Operation Gridlock, while wearing their scrubs and [[N95 mask|N95 face masks]]. One nurse who participated in the counter-protest stated the protest felt like \"a slap in the face to medical workers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/health-care-workers-took-stand-against-protestors-opposing-coronavirus-lockdown-n1187711|title=Health care workers stand against protesters opposing coronavirus lockdown in Colorado|last=Kesslen|first=Ben|date=April 20, 2020|website=NBC News|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> The nurses stood in the crosswalk during red lights as a reminder to why the shut down measures were needed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/photos-purportedly-show-coronavirus-protest-standoff|title=Coronavirus standoff: Photos purportedly show Colorado health care workers at odds with anti-lockdown protesters|last=Norman|first=Greg|date=2020-04-20|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n=== Idaho ===\nSeveral hundred protesters assembled at the [[Idaho State Capitol]] buildiing in Boise under the slogan \"Disobey Idaho\" on April 17. The  protest was organized byby three conservative groups \u2014 the \"Idaho Freedom Foundation\", \"Idaho Second Amendment Alliance\" and \"Health Freedom Idaho\" and emceed by [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] [[Idaho Legislature|state representative]] [[Tammy Nichols]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bustillo|first=Ximena|url=https://www.idahostatesman.com/news/coronavirus/article242092321.html|title=Hundreds rally at Idaho Capitol to protest Gov. Little\u2019s stay-home order|date=Mar 17, 2020|work=Idaho Statesman|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/hundreds-defy-idahos-stay-at-home-order-at-capitol-protest/2020/04/17/04cf4480-80fa-11ea-84c2-0792d8591911_story.html|title=Hundreds defy Idaho\u2019s stay-at-home order at Capitol protest|last=AP|first=Rebecca Boone {{!}}|website=Washington Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n===Indiana===\nOn Saturday, April 18, approximately 250<ref name=\"IndyStar\">{{cite news |last1=Pak-Harvey |first1=Amelia |title=Protesters rally outside Governor's Residence to say Holcomb's orders go too far |url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/local/marion-county/2020/04/18/indiana-coronavirus-protesters-say-gov-holcombs-orders-go-too-far/5148983002/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Indianapolis Star |agency=Ganett |date=18 April 2020}}</ref> people gathered  in front of the Governor's Mansion in [[Indianapolis]] to protest Governor [[Eric Holcomb]]'s stay at home order.  The protesters did not follow social distancing guidelines, although some wore [[Face masks during the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|face masks]].  The protesters called for the Governor to appear and explain himself, and said they were willing to be arrested if necessary.<ref name=\"Indiana\">{{cite news |last1=Staff Report |title=Dozens protest Indiana \u2018stay at home\u2019 order outside governor\u2019s mansion |url=https://www.wishtv.com/news/indiana-news/dozens-protest-indiana-stay-at-home-order-outside-governors-mansion/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=WISH TV |date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Kentucky===\nDozens of people gathered on the lawn of the state capitol in [[Frankfort, Kentucky|Frankfort]] in the afternoon of Wednesday, April 15, 2020 to protest Governor [[Andy Beshear]]'s anti-coronavirus measures. They could also be heard inside the capitol building. Throughout Governor Beshea 's one-hour press briefing, the protesters chanted continuously and occasionally blew a horn. The principal demand was that businesses in the State be reopened.<ref name=\"kara_b_and_paul_e_15\">{{cite news|last1=Berg|first1=Kara|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/04/15/lansing-capitol-protest-michigan-stay-home-order/5139472002/|title=Thousands Converge to Protest Michigan Governor's Stay-Home Order in 'Operation Gridlock'|date=April 15, 2020|work=USA Today|access-date=April 15, 2020|last2=Egan|first2=Paul|last-author-amp=yes}}</ref>\n\n===Michigan===\n{{Main|2020 Lansing, Michigan protest}}\nThousands of people protested, mainly in cars, in a protest they called [[2020 Lansing, Michigan protest|\"Operation Gridlock\"]] in the vicinity of the [[Michigan State Capitol]] in [[Lansing, Michigan]], on April 15, 2020.<ref name=\"kara_b_and_paul_e_15\" /> Protesters had arrived by 9:00 am and the protest was ongoing, although shrinking, at 4:30 pm.<ref name=\"heatherwalk_15\">{{cite news|last=Walker|first=Heather|url=https://www.upmatters.com/news/protesters-in-opposition-of-stay-home-order-gather-at-michigan-capitol/|title='Free MI': Stay-home order protesters gather at Capitol|date=April 15, 2020|work=UP Matters|access-date=April 17, 2020|publisher=[[WJMN-TV]]|location=Marquette, Michigan}}</ref>\n\n===North Carolina===\nIn [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh]], people protested outside the capitol building on Tuesday, April 14, 2020. Some were arrested.<ref name=\"gabriel_sanch_15\">{{cite news|last=Sanchez|first=Gabriel H.|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/gabrielsanchez/huge-crowds-protest-coronavirus-trump-coronavirus-pandemic|title=These Pictures Show Huge Crowds Protesting Against Coronavirus Lockdowns at State Capitols|date=April 16, 2020|work=Buzzfeed News|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Ohio===\n[[File:Columbus coronavirus protests at the Ohio Statehouse, 2020-04-18j.jpg|thumb|An anti-lockdown protest at the [[Ohio Statehouse]], April 18, 2020]]\n\nProtests began in Ohio on April 9 with about 75 gathering outside of the statehouse and occurred again on the 13th growing to a group of 200-300.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite news|author=Cincinnati CityBeat Staff|url=https://www.clevescene.com/scene-and-heard/archives/2020/04/14/were-not-afraid-of-any-virus-crowds-gathered-outside-of-ohio-statehouse-protesting-coronavirus-shutdowns|title='We're Not Afraid of Any Virus': Crowds Gathered Outside of Ohio Statehouse Protesting Coronavirus Shutdowns|date=April 14, 2020|work=Cleveland Scene|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe following weekend, Protests began on Friday, April 17 with dozens protesting outside the east side of the Statehouse.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dispatch.com/photogallery/OH/20200418/PHOTOGALLERY/418009999/PH/1|title=Photos: Protests over stay-at-home orders at Ohio Statehouse|website=The Columbus Dispatch|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> The next day, April 18, the protests grew to hundreds who came to protest Governor DeWine's stay at home order.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/open/2020/04/hundreds-protest-in-columbus-against-ohio-coronavirus-restrictions.html|title=Hundreds protest in Columbus against Ohio coronavirus restrictions|last=Hancock|first=Laura|last2=clevel|date=2020-04-18|website=cleveland|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20|last3=.com}}</ref><ref name=\":4\" />  Protesters carried signs concerned with the loss of liberties for the sake of safety, as well as signs critical of State officials,<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> and demanded that the State be immediately reopened.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\nThe Governor has said that he will not interfere with the protests, at least provided they adhere to social distancing guidelines.<ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/ohio-governor-protests-are-ok-if-protestors-socially-distance-2020-4|title=Ohio governor says anti-lockdown protests are OK if protestors adhere to social distancing|last=Perrett|first=Connor|website=Business Insider|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>  Photographs from the protests on April 18 indicate that not all of protesters had been.<ref name=\":6\" /> Though, the protests also involved those who stayed in cars.<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n\n===Oregon===\nIn Oregon, dozens of protesters circled the Oregon State Capitol in Salem in their vehicles on April 17, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.registerguard.com/news/20200418/coronavirus-updates-saturday-dozens-protest-oregonrsquos-stay-at-home-order-butte-to-butte-race-canceled|title=Coronavirus updates, Saturday: Dozens protest Oregon's stay-at-home order; Butte to Butte race canceled|first=Staff, news|last=services|website=The Register-Guard}}</ref> 200 people gathered outside City Hall in [[Redmond, Oregon|Redmond]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ktvz.com/news/2020/04/17/protest-planned-in-redmond-against-stay-at-home-order/|title=More than 200 gather in Redmond to protest stay-at-home order|first1=Max|last1=Goldwasser|first2=The Associated|last2=Press|date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bendbulletin.com/coronavirus/redmond-activist-to-protest-oregon-stay-home-order-with-rally/article_ce398714-8040-11ea-83b4-97b0b821091c.html|title=Redmond activist to protest Oregon stay home order with rally|first=GARRETT ANDREWS The|last=Bulletin|website=The Bulletin}}</ref>\n\nThe \"Re-Open Oregon\" rally is planned for May 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koin.com/news/health/coronavirus/open-oregon-rally-arrives-in-salem/|title=\u2018Open Oregon\u2019 rally in Salem: \u2018No light at end of tunnel\u2019|date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portlandmercury.com/blogtown/2020/04/16/28299387/conservative-protestors-plan-reopen-oregon-rally-at-state-capitol|title=Conservative Protestors Plan \"Reopen Oregon\" Rally at State Capitol|first1=Blair Stenvick \u2022|last1=Apr 16|first2=2020 at 11:16|last2=Am|website=Portland Mercury}}</ref>\n\n=== Pennsylvania ===\nOn [[Patriots' Day]], April 20, hundreds of protesters marched on the state capital building during a Monday morning \u201cOperation Gridlock Pennsylvania\u201d event  in [[Harrisburg, Pennsylvania|Harrisburg]].<ref name=\"olson1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/hundreds-of-protesters-line-harrisburg-streets-in-protest-against-stay-at-home-order|title=Hundreds of protesters line Harrisburg streets in rowdy protest against stay-at-home order|last=Olson|first=Tyler|date=2020-04-20|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> The protest was  organized by three groups, \u201cRe-open Pennsylvania,\u201d \u201cEnd the Lockdown Pennsylvania,\u201d and \u201cPennsylvania Against Excessive Quarantine\u201d led in part by an Ohio-based 2nd amendment rights activist named Chris Dorr.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc27.com/news/local/harrisburg/thousands-of-protesters-expected-at-a-reopen-rally/|title=Thousands of protesters expected at a \u2018reopen rally\u2019|date=2020-04-20|website=ABC27|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref name=\"olson1\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailyitem.com/news/update-hundreds-gather-at-capitol-in-harrisburg-for-anti-shutdown-rally-calling-to-reopen-pennsylvania/article_7d4f6946-831e-11ea-b61e-3f87f608ab01.html|title=UPDATE Hundreds gather at Capitol in Harrisburg for anti-shutdown rally calling to \u2018reopen\u2019 Pennsylvania|last=PA|first=Cynthia Fernandez of Spotlight|website=The Daily Item|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>  \n\n=== Texas ===\nOn Saturday, April 18, hundreds protested at the statehouse in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]] at a \"You Can't Close America\" rally organized by ''[[InfoWars]]''{{'}} [[Alex Jones]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/alex-jones-coronavirus-lockdown-protest-texas-anthony-fauci-fire-a9472611.html|title=Alex Jones joins protest against coronavirus lockdown orders as crowds chant \u2018Fire Fauci\u2019|date=2020-04-18|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n===Washington===\nIn Washington State, the Kitsap County Republican Party coordinated the event \"Hazardous Liberty! Defend the Constitution!\" in Olympia on April 19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://komonews.com/news/coronavirus/protest-against-state-closure-planned-for-tomorrow-in-olympia|title=Protest against state closure planned for tomorrow in Olympia|first=Cole Miller &#124; KOMO|last=News|date=April 18, 2020|website=KOMO}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.king5.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/people-plan-to-gather-in-olympia-sunday-to-protest-gov-inslees-stay-at-home-order/281-d7920d24-f6b8-4b75-b63d-27bd8b605d0b|title=People plan to gather in Olympia Sunday to protest Gov. Inslee\u2019s stay-at-home order|website=KING}}</ref> the Olympia event was attended by over 2,000 people.<ref>\"Demonstrators rally in Olympia against Washington\u2019s coronavirus stay-at-home order\", The Seattle Times, April 20, 2020, page 1</ref>\n\n== Response ==\nOn April 16 President [[Donald Trump]] issued guidelines for how to phase out restrictions, saying that governors would decide how to reopen their own states and suggesting a cautious three-phase approach.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/04/16/politics/donald-trump-reopening-guidelines-coronavirus/index.html|title=Trump completes reversal, telling govs 'you are going to call your own shots' and distributes new guidelines|date=April 16, 2020|work=CNN|accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref> The next day he reacted to the protests against social restrictions by encouraging the protests, tweeting \"LIBERATE MICHIGAN!\" and \"LIBERATE MINNESOTA!\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/17/us/politics/trump-coronavirus-governors.html|title=Trump Encourages Protest Against Governors Who Have Imposed Virus Restrictions|last1=Shear|first1=Michael D.|last2=Mervosh|first2=Sarah|date=April 17, 2020|work=The New York Times|accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Itkowitz|first=Colby|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2020/04/17/liberate-trump-tweets-support-protesting-against-stay-at-home-orders/|title='Liberate': Trump Tweets Support of Protests Against Stay-at-Home Orders|date=April 17, 2020|work=[[The Washington Post]]|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/17/us/coronavirus-cases-news-update.html|title=Trump Foments Protests Against Governors; Experts Warn of Testing Shortages|date=2020-04-17|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-18|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> [[Jay Inslee|Governor Jay Inslee]] (D-WA) accused the President of \"fomenting domestic rebellion\" with these tweets: \"The president's statements this morning encourage illegal and dangerous acts. He is putting millions of people in danger of contracting [[COVID-19]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/trump-accused-fomenting-rebellion-liberate-tweets-200417223606672.html|title=Trump accused of 'fomenting rebellion' after 'LIBERATE' tweets|website=www.aljazeera.com|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref> On [[This Week (American TV program)|ABC's This Week]] two days later, Inslee said the President's call to ignore his own team's guidelines was \"schizophrenic.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2020/04/19/governors-decry-trump-call-liberate-states-coronavirus-restrictions/5162196002/|title=Governors slam Trump's call to 'liberate' states where protesters object to coronavirus restrictions|last=Cummings|first=William|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nTrump has continued to encourage the protesters' defiance of [[social distancing]] orders by saying  \"They seem very responsible to me.\"<ref>{{Cite news|last=Reuters/AP|first=Source:|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2020/apr/18/they-seem-very-responsible-to-me-trump-defends-anti-lockdown-protesters-video|title='They seem very responsible to me': Trump defends anti-lockdown protesters - video|date=2020-04-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-19|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> [[Stephen Moore (writer)|Stephen Moore]], a right-wing member of his economic council, stoked [[List of incidents of xenophobia and racism related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|racial passions]] by comparing the protesters to [[Rosa Parks]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/493484-trump-ally-compares-coronavirus-protesters-to-rosa-parks|title=Trump ally compares coronavirus protesters to Rosa Parks|last=Johnson|first=Martin|date=2020-04-18|website=TheHill|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n[[Facebook]] has started blocking events and messages from anti-quarantine protest groups \"when gatherings do not follow the health parameters established by the government and are therefore unlawful.\" The Governors of [[Phil Murphy|New Jersey]] and [[Pete Ricketts|Nebraska]] have stated that they have not requested that Facebook take the posts down. The company appears to be doing it on their own volition but [[Donald Trump Jr.|Donald Trump, Jr.]] claims they are \"[[colluding]] with state governments to quash [[Freedom of speech|free speech]].\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/20/facebook-shuts-down-anti-quarantine-protests-at-states-request-196143|title=Republicans attack Facebook as network shuts down anti-lockdown protests|last=Overly|first=Steven|website=POLITICO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on politics]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States}}\n\n[[Category:2020 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States]]\n[[Category:Protests in the United States]]\n[[Category:Protests over responses to the 2020 coronavirus pandemic| ]]\n", "name_user": "Kire1975", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBackground:cleanup language", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protests_over_responses_to_the_2020_coronavirus_pandemic"}
{"title_page": "Hong Kong\u2013Taiwan relations", "text_new": "{{short description|Relationship between Hong Kong and Taiwan}}\n{{Expand Chinese|\u53f0\u7063\u8207\u9999\u6e2f\u95dc\u4fc2|date=October 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox Bilateral relations|Hong Kong\u2013Taiwan|Hong Kong|Taiwan|map=Hong_Kong_Taiwan_Locator.png|mission1=[[Taipei Economic and Cultural Office in Hong Kong]]|mission2=[[Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office (Taiwan)|Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office]], [[Taipei]]}}\n\n'''Relations with [[Hong Kong]] and the [[Taiwan|Republic of China]] (Taiwan)''' are on a high level. \n\n== History ==\nBefore 1842, both regions were part of the [[Qing dynasty]]; in 1842, Hong Kong Island was ceded to the [[British Empire]] as a result of the [[First Opium War]], and in 1895, Taiwan was ceded to the [[Empire of Japan]] as a result of the [[First Sino-Japanese War]]. [[Sun Yat-sen]] was a student in Hong Kong in the late 1800s and believed that the Qing dynasty's ineffectiveness and loss in the First Sino-Japanese War necessitated a revolution to replace Chinese dynasties with a modern republic, and began the formation of the [[Revive China Society]] in 1894 to overthrow the Qing dynasty. The Revive China Society was headquartered at 13 Staunton Street<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amo.gov.hk/en/trails_sheungwan2.php?tid=4|title=Original Site of Xing Zhong Hui (Revive China Society) Hong Kong Headquarters|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> in Hong Kong, and in 1905 it was merged with other groups to form the [[Tongmenghui]]. This organization had wide support among Chinese, and played a key role<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://schoolhistory.co.uk/notes/xinhai-revolution/|title=Xinhai Revolution {{!}} Facts, Summary, Uprising, Revolution & Aftermath|website=School History|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> in uprisings started by revolutionaries, including the [[Xinhai Revolution]] in 1911, which overthrew the Qing dynasty. After the success of the Xinhai Revolution, Sun Yat-sen [[History of the Republic of China|declared the establishment]] of the Republic of China on 1 January 1912, and was inaugurated as the first provisional president. Later that same year in August 1912, the Tongmenghui merged with other groups to [[History of the Kuomintang|create the Kuomintang]] (Nationalist Party), and Sun Yat-sen was chosen as its leader.\n\nSun Yat-sen returned to Hong Kong in 1923 to visit the [[University of Hong Kong]], which had incorporated the [[Hong Kong College of Medicine for Chinese]] as its medical school, of which Sun Yat-sen was an early alumni. During his visit at HKU, he gave a speech<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://100.hku.hk/sunyatsen/address_ENG.html|title=The Man\uff0eThe University\uff0eThe History - Sun Yat-sen|website=100.hku.hk|access-date=2020-01-07}}</ref> and declared Hong Kong's inspiration to him in the revolutions that eventually created the Republic of China: \"That is the answer to the question, where did I get my revolutionary ideas: it is entirely in Hong Kong.\" With Sun Yat-sen's death in 1925, [[Chiang Kai-shek|Chaing Kai-shek]] became leader of the KMT and Sun Yat-sen's successor, eventually [[Northeast Flag Replacement|unifying China]] under the Nationalist government in 1928. \n[[File:1945 liberation of Hong Kong at Cenotaph.jpg|thumb|Republic of China flag flying in Hong Kong at the Cenotaph on Liberation Day in 1945]]\nIn 1941, as the Japanese military advanced towards Hong Kong, UK Prime Minister [[Winston Churchill]] was reluctant to defend the colony, and said that defensive troops should be reduced to a \"symbolical scale\" there.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/article/2059530/why-churchill-didnt-want-hong-kong-defended-against-japanese-and-how|title=Why Churchill didn\u2019t want Hong Kong defended against Japanese|date=2017-01-07|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-01-07}}</ref> With a [[Battle of Hong Kong|quick victory]] by the Japanese against the weakly-defended colony, the [[Japanese occupation of Hong Kong]] began, and both Hong Kong and Taiwan were subjects of the Empire of Japan. Before the surrender of Japan at the end of [[World War II]], U.S. President [[Franklin D. Roosevelt|Franklin Roosevelt]] promised [[Soong Mei-ling]], wife of Chaing Kai-shek, that Hong Kong would be restored to Republic of China control. This was in line with longstanding United States policy; the United States, in 1899 had advocated the [[Open Door Policy]], which communicated that China should not be partitioned and colonized. The [[Nine-Power Treaty]] in 1922, signed by the British, affirmed the Open Door Policy and territorial integrity of China. In July of 1940, Winston Churchill declared in Parliament that \"We desire to see China's status and integrity preserved, and as was indicated in our Note of 14th January, 1939, we are ready to negotiate with the Chinese Government, after the conclusion of peace, the abolition of extraterritorial rights, the rendition of concessions and the revision of treaties on the basis of reciprocity and equality<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://api.parliament.uk/historic-hansard/commons/1940/jul/18/transit-of-war-material-to-china|title=TRANSIT OF WAR MATERIAL TO CHINA. (Hansard, 18 July 1940)|website=api.parliament.uk|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref>,\" affirming territorial integrity and relinquishment of extra-territorial rights in China. The idea of territorial integrity and [[decolonization]] was further encapsulated in the 1941 [[Atlantic Charter]] statement, issued by Franklin Roosevelt (who was staunchly against colonialism<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.americanheritage.com/hell-hole-yours|title=\u201cThat Hell-hole Of Yours\u201d {{!}} AMERICAN HERITAGE|website=www.americanheritage.com|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>) and Winston Churchill, stipulating that \"territorial adjustments must be in accord with the wishes of the peoples concerned.\" Though Winston Churchill did not want British colonies to decolonize, he agreed to the Atlantic Charter's decolonization provisions \"to get the Americans into the war\" with military aid on the side of the Allies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://history.state.gov/milestones/1937-1945/atlantic-conf|title=Milestones: 1937\u20131945 - Office of the Historian|website=history.state.gov|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> On January 1st 1942, the [[Declaration by United Nations|Declaration of the United Nations]] was signed by the [[Four Policemen|Big Four]] (the United States, United Kingdom, Soviet Union, and Republic of China), stipulating that the Atlantic Charter's pledges should be upheld. This became the basis of the [[Charter of the United Nations]] in 1945.\n\nDespite the weak protection of Hong Kong and agreements by the British to the Nine-Power Treaty, Atlantic Charter, and Declaration of the United Nations, at the end of the war, the British did not want to see Hong Kong handed over to the Republic of China, and moved quickly to [[Japanese occupation of Hong Kong#Post-war political stage|regain control]] of Hong Kong<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.endofempire.asia/0828-liberating-hong-kong-3/|title=Liberating Hong Kong|date=2015-08-28|website=End of Empire|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> in [[Liberation Day (Hong Kong)|1945]], preventing the unification of Hong Kong and the Republic of China (ROC). After the loss in the [[Chinese Civil War]] in 1949, the Koumintang-ruled Republic of China government, started by Sun Yat-sen, fled to Taiwan in [[Republic of China retreat to Taiwan|the Great Retreat]]. Shortly after, on 6 January 1950, the [[China\u2013United Kingdom relations|UK recognized]] the [[China|People's Republic of China]] (PRC) as the government of China due to economic interests, and blocked the Republic of China government from participating in the [[Treaty of San Francisco]] in 1951, which introduced the [[Political status of Taiwan|issue]] of which government Taiwan was to be surrendered to. Furthermore, in 1971, [[United Nations General Assembly Resolution 2758]] was supported by the British and passed, recognizing the PRC as the legitimate government of [[China and the United Nations|China in the UN]] rather than the Republic of China. Afterwards, the British and People's Republic of China began negotiations on the [[Handover of Hong Kong]], ultimately sealing Hong Kong's future with the PRC rather than the ROC.\n\nBoth during and after the Chinese Civil War, many people from Mainland China, including pro-Kuomintang refugees and former soldiers, fled to both [[1950s in Hong Kong|Hong Kong]] and Taiwan.  After the Civil War, the [[Pro-Taiwan camp (Hong Kong)|Pro-Taiwan camp]] was a major political force in Hong Kong, and many emigrants settled at [[Tiu Keng Leng|Rennie's Mill]], nicknamed \"Little Taiwan.\" On [[National Day of the Republic of China|Double Ten Day]], flags of the Republic of China were frequently seen in Hong Kong; the ordering of the removal<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/magazines/post-magazine/article/2025663/what-sparked-hong-kongs-double-tenth-riots|title=What sparked Hong Kong\u2019s Double Tenth riots|date=2016-10-07|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref> of one flag by a junior government official caused the [[Hong Kong 1956 riots|Hong Kong 1956 Riots]], when pro-Nationalists (called \"Rightists\") fought against [[Pro-Beijing camp (Hong Kong)|Pro-Communists]] (called \"Leftists\"). Though the flying of the Republic of China flag during Double Ten Day flag has decreased since the 1997 handover, it can still be seen to this day<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3032422/hong-kong-protesters-gather-mark-taiwans-celebration-108th|title=Hong Kong protesters gather to mark Taiwan\u2019s \u2018Double Tenth\u2019 holiday|date=2019-10-10|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/video/china/2114867/double-tenth-day-disappearing-flags-republic-china-hong-kong|title=Double Tenth day: the disappearing flags of the Republic of China in Hong Kong|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref> at places including [[Red House (Hong Kong)|Hung Lau]] in Tuen Mun, where an obelisk and bust of Sun Yat-sen are located. Hong Kong and Taiwan invested heavily in education and infrastructure after World War II, causing both economies to significantly improve and be part of the [[Four Asian Tigers]].\n\n== Official relations and politics ==\nSince 2010, the relationship between Hong Kong and the ROC is managed through the [[Hong Kong-Taiwan Economic and Cultural Co-operation and Promotion Council]] (ECCPC) and [[Taiwan-Hong Kong Economic and Cultural Co-operation Council]] (ECCC). Meanwhile, the [[Taipei Economic and Cultural Office in Hong Kong]] (TECO) is the representative office of the Republic of China in Hong Kong, while the [[Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office (Taiwan)|Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office]] (HKETCO) is the representative office of Hong Kong in the Republic of China.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20031126025622/http://www.eslisland.com/guide/TaiwanEmbassiesabroad.htm Taiwanese Overseas 'Embassies' Abroad]</ref> In addition, the relations with Hong Kong is also conducted by the [[Mainland Affairs Council]], although not all regulations applicable to mainland China are automatically applied to those territories.\n\nIn recent times, both regions have been involved with each other politically. In 2014, students from Hong Kong supported Taiwan's [[Sunflower Student Movement]], and students from Taiwan supported the [[Umbrella Movement]] in Hong Kong.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/article/1595514/occupy-takes-seed-idea-sunflower-movement|title=Occupy takes seed of an idea from sunflower movement|date=2014-09-19|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> The [[Murder of Poon Hiu-wing|2018 murder by a Hong Kong citizen while in Taiwan]] caused the Hong Kong government to propose the [[2019 Hong Kong extradition bill|Hong Kong extradition bill]] in 2019, which would have allowed suspected criminals to be extradited to not just Taiwan, but Mainland China and Macau as well. This began massive [[2019 Hong Kong protests|protests]] in Hong Kong, with the government of Taiwan supporting the protesters, not wanting the proposal to become law.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1642413/why-taiwan-is-so-outspoken-on-hong-kongs-extradition-law/|title=Why Taiwan is the most outspoken critic of Hong Kong\u2019s extradition law|last=Steger|first=Isabella|website=Quartz|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> The government of Taiwan sees the extradition bill, now withdrawn, as an infringement of the [[one country, two systems]] principle, which has been the PRC's proposal for [[Chinese unification|unification]] with Taiwan. Tens of thousands of Taiwanese citizens marched in Taipei on 29 September 2019 in support of Hong Kong's pro-democracy movement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://focustaiwan.tw/news/acs/201909290011.aspx|title=Huge crowd rallies in Taipei to support Hong Kong democracy movement|website=focustaiwan.tw|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> Because of Taiwan's support of the protests, ROC flags have been frequently seen at protests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3032422/hong-kong-protesters-gather-mark-taiwans-celebration-108th|title=Hong Kong protesters gather to mark Taiwan\u2019s \u2018Double Tenth\u2019 holiday|date=2019-10-10|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> \n\n[[Joshua Wong]], a politician from Hong Kong, has also traveled to Taiwan to meet with the government to discuss the potential for Hong Kong protesters to seek political asylum in Taiwan<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/hong-kongs-joshua-wong-visits-taiwan-to-meet-with-ruling-party|title=Activist Joshua Wong urges Taiwanese to show support for Hong Kong|last=hermesauto|date=2019-09-03|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3025914/taiwans-refugee-bill-does-not-apply-hong-kong-protesters-now|title=Refugee bill does not apply to Hong Kong protesters for now, Taiwan says|date=2019-09-05|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref>. Keith Fong Chung-yin, president of the [[Hong Kong Baptist University]] Student Union, also echoed Joshua Wong's remarks about the lack of an asylum process in Taiwan and says the [[Democratic Progressive Party]] (DPP) has not enacted specific laws to help refugees<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/3832989|title=HK student leader says Taiwan\u2019s asylum ...|last=News|first=Taiwan|website=Taiwan News|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3041497/taiwanese-president-tsai-ing-wen-denies-using-hong-kong|title=Taiwanese president Tsai denies \u2018using\u2019 Hong Kong protests for election|date=2019-12-10|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>. Though [[Tsai Ing-wen]], the president of Taiwan, has regularly supported the protesters on social media and Article 18 of Taiwan's Laws and Regulations Regarding Hong Kong & Macao Affairs stipulates that \"Necessary assistance shall be provided to Hong Kong or Macau Residents whose safety and liberty are immediately threatened for political reasons<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mac.gov.tw/en/News_Content.aspx?n=2EA6ADFC159E7A0D&sms=8675D7361543DE23&s=52C62C35EEFEE30A&Create=1|title=Act Governing Relations with Hong Kong and Macau|date=2018-08-14|website=Mainland Affairs Council|language=en|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref>,\" the government of Taiwan has not created a process for political refugees yet<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thediplomat.com/2019/10/friends-from-hong-kong-taiwans-refugee-problem/|title=Friends from Hong Kong: Taiwan\u2019s Refugee Problem|website=thediplomat.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/11/26/781668197/some-hong-kong-protesters-are-seeking-refuge-in-taiwan-for-taiwan-its-complicate|title=Some Hong Kong Protesters Are Seeking Refuge In Taiwan. For Taiwan, It's Complicated|website=NPR.org|language=en|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref>.  [[Joseph Wu]], Taiwan's [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Republic of China)|Minister of Foreign Affairs]], has said that existing legislation to deal with refugees is sufficient<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/ap-interview-taiwan-may-help-111618072.html|title=AP Interview: Taiwan may help if Hong Kong violence expands|website=news.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>, even though a New York Times video<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/video/world/asia/100000006864895/hong-kong-protests-taiwan-secret-network.html|title=Protesters Are Fleeing Hong Kong. A Secret Network Is Helping Them.|last=Times|first=The New York|date=2019-12-08|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-12-11|language=English|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> has shown that some refugees from Hong Kong have entered Taiwan illegally, providing evidence that existing legislation is not sufficient. In response to the New York Times video, the [[Mainland Affairs Council]] warned protesters to not enter Taiwan illegally, and reiterated the statement that existing laws are sufficient<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1496709-20191209.htm?|title=HK protesters warned not to flee to Taiwan illegally - RTHK|website=news.rthk.hk|language=en-gb|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>, even though they only cover special cases, such as student, investment, and tourist visas. This lack of a formal asylum process means that refugees who do not qualify for student and investment visas enter Taiwan on 30-day tourist visas<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/08/world/asia/hong-kong-taiwan-protests.html|title=\u2018We Are Fleeing the Law\u2019: Hong Kong Protesters Escape to Taiwan|date=2019-12-08|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-12-11|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenation.com/article/taiwan-refugee-china-hongkong/|title=Why Taiwan Won\u2019t Welcome China\u2019s Dissidents|last=Aspinwall|first=Nick|date=2019-12-06|access-date=2020-01-05|language=en-US|issn=0027-8378}}</ref> and cannot legally work in Taiwan; despite this, some in Hong Kong have fled to Taiwan, including [[Causeway Bay Books]] founder [[Lam Wing-kee]]. In addition, Taiwan's Ministry of Education in November of 2019 announced that university students in Hong Kong would be allowed to attend lectures and continue their studies in Taiwan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3038634/taiwans-universities-open-doors-students-fleeing-hong-kong|title=Taiwan universities open doors to students fleeing Hong Kong|date=2019-11-21|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref> In contrast to the DPP's position of believing current laws are adequate, [[Han Kuo-yu]], the Kuomintang's candidate for the [[2020 Taiwan presidential election]], has said that he fully supports the passage of a refugee law to help asylum seekers from Hong Kong.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-protests-taiwan-idUSKBN1YG15K|title=Enact refugee law to help Hong Kong, Taiwan presidential hopeful says|date=2019-12-12|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-12-12|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Cultural ==\nCulturally, though the primary regional language of Hong Kong is [[Cantonese]] and the primary language of Taiwan is [[Mandarin Chinese|Mandarin]], both regions continue to use [[Traditional Chinese characters]], in contrast to [[Simplified Chinese characters]].\n\nAs a result of the war, no direct flights were allowed between Taiwan and Mainland China; thus many passengers transferred through Hong Kong until 2003, when the [[Cross-Strait charter]] was created. Travel between nationals of the two regions is popular; in 2018, there were approximately 1.7 million nationals of Taiwan who traveled to Hong Kong, the third-most destination after Japan (4.8 million) and Mainland China (4.1 million).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://admin.taiwan.net.tw/English/FileUploadCategoryListE003130.aspx?CategoryID=cde3e78b-82f0-4df9-8b88-c9c9e2cc08ac&appname=FileUploadCategoryListE003130|title=Tourism Statistics|last=\u4ea4\u901a\u90e8\u89c0\u5149\u5c40\u884c\u653f\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7db2|website=admin.taiwan.net.tw|language=en-us|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> These 1.7 million nationals represented Hong Kong's second-most inbound tourists, only after tourists from Mainland China.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tourism.gov.hk/english/statistics/statistics_perform.html|title=Tourism Commission - Tourism Performance|website=www.tourism.gov.hk|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> Non-stop flights are operated between [[Hong Kong International Airport|Hong Kong]] and Taipei ([[Taoyuan International Airport|Taoyuan]]), [[Taichung International Airport|Taichung]], [[Tainan Airport|Tainan]], and [[Kaohsiung International Airport|Kaohsiung]] airports.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Cross-Strait relations]]\n*[[Foreign relations of Hong Kong]]\n*[[Foreign relations of Taiwan]]\n*[[Pro-Taiwan camp (Hong Kong)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Foreign relations of Hong Kong}}\n{{Foreign relations of the Republic of China (Taiwan)}}\n{{Cross-Strait relations}}\n\n{{Hong Kong-stub}}\n{{Taiwan-poli-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Hong Kong\u2013Taiwan relations| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Relationship between Hong Kong and Taiwan}}\n{{Expand Chinese|\u53f0\u7063\u8207\u9999\u6e2f\u95dc\u4fc2|date=October 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox Bilateral relations|Hong Kong\u2013Taiwan|Hong Kong|Taiwan|map=Hong_Kong_Taiwan_Locator.png|mission1=[[Taipei Economic and Cultural Office in Hong Kong]]|mission2=[[Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office (Taiwan)|Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office]], [[Taipei]]}}\n\n'''Relations with [[Hong Kong]] and the [[Taiwan|Republic of China]] (Taiwan)''' are on a high level. \n\n== History ==\nBefore 1842, both regions were part of the [[Qing dynasty]]; in 1842, Hong Kong Island was ceded to the [[British Empire]] as a result of the [[First Opium War]], and in 1895, Taiwan was ceded to the [[Empire of Japan]] as a result of the [[First Sino-Japanese War]]. [[Sun Yat-sen]] was a student in Hong Kong in the late 1800s and believed that the Qing dynasty's ineffectiveness and loss in the First Sino-Japanese War necessitated a revolution to replace Chinese dynasties with a modern republic, and began the formation of the [[Revive China Society]] in 1894 to overthrow the Qing dynasty. The Revive China Society was headquartered at 13 Staunton Street<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amo.gov.hk/en/trails_sheungwan2.php?tid=4|title=Original Site of Xing Zhong Hui (Revive China Society) Hong Kong Headquarters|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> in Hong Kong, and in 1905 it was merged with other groups to form the [[Tongmenghui]]. This organization had wide support among Chinese, and played a key role<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://schoolhistory.co.uk/notes/xinhai-revolution/|title=Xinhai Revolution {{!}} Facts, Summary, Uprising, Revolution & Aftermath|website=School History|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> in uprisings started by revolutionaries, including the [[Xinhai Revolution]] in 1911, which overthrew the Qing dynasty. After the success of the Xinhai Revolution, Sun Yat-sen [[History of the Republic of China|declared the establishment]] of the Republic of China on 1 January 1912, and was inaugurated as the first provisional president. Later that same year in August 1912, the Tongmenghui merged with other groups to [[History of the Kuomintang|create the Kuomintang]] (Nationalist Party), and Sun Yat-sen was chosen as its leader.\n\nSun Yat-sen returned to Hong Kong in 1923 to visit the [[University of Hong Kong]], which had incorporated the [[Hong Kong College of Medicine for Chinese]] as its medical school, of which Sun Yat-sen was an early alumni. During his visit at HKU, he gave a speech<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://100.hku.hk/sunyatsen/address_ENG.html|title=The Man\uff0eThe University\uff0eThe History - Sun Yat-sen|website=100.hku.hk|access-date=2020-01-07}}</ref> and declared Hong Kong's inspiration to him in the revolutions that eventually created the Republic of China: \"That is the answer to the question, where did I get my revolutionary ideas: it is entirely in Hong Kong.\" With Sun Yat-sen's death in 1925, [[Chiang Kai-shek|Chaing Kai-shek]] became leader of the KMT and Sun Yat-sen's successor, eventually [[Northeast Flag Replacement|unifying China]] under the Nationalist government in 1928. \n\nIn 1941, as the Japanese military advanced towards Hong Kong, UK Prime Minister [[Winston Churchill]] was reluctant to defend the colony, and said that defensive troops should be reduced to a \"symbolical scale\" there.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/article/2059530/why-churchill-didnt-want-hong-kong-defended-against-japanese-and-how|title=Why Churchill didn\u2019t want Hong Kong defended against Japanese|date=2017-01-07|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-01-07}}</ref> With a [[Battle of Hong Kong|quick victory]] by the Japanese against the weakly-defended colony, the [[Japanese occupation of Hong Kong]] began, and both Hong Kong and Taiwan were subjects of the Empire of Japan. Before the surrender of Japan at the end of [[World War II]], U.S. President [[Franklin D. Roosevelt|Franklin Roosevelt]] promised [[Soong Mei-ling]], wife of Chaing Kai-shek, that Hong Kong would be restored to Republic of China control. This was in line with longstanding United States policy; the United States, in 1899 had advocated the [[Open Door Policy]], which communicated that China should not be partitioned and colonized. The [[Nine-Power Treaty]] in 1922, signed by the British, affirmed the Open Door Policy and territorial integrity of China. In July of 1940, Winston Churchill declared in Parliament that \"We desire to see China's status and integrity preserved, and as was indicated in our Note of 14th January, 1939, we are ready to negotiate with the Chinese Government, after the conclusion of peace, the abolition of extraterritorial rights, the rendition of concessions and the revision of treaties on the basis of reciprocity and equality<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://api.parliament.uk/historic-hansard/commons/1940/jul/18/transit-of-war-material-to-china|title=TRANSIT OF WAR MATERIAL TO CHINA. (Hansard, 18 July 1940)|website=api.parliament.uk|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref>,\" affirming territorial integrity and relinquishment of extra-territorial rights in China. The idea of territorial integrity and [[decolonization]] was further encapsulated in the 1941 [[Atlantic Charter]] statement, issued by Franklin Roosevelt (who was staunchly against colonialism<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.americanheritage.com/hell-hole-yours|title=\u201cThat Hell-hole Of Yours\u201d {{!}} AMERICAN HERITAGE|website=www.americanheritage.com|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>) and Winston Churchill, stipulating that \"territorial adjustments must be in accord with the wishes of the peoples concerned.\" Though Winston Churchill did not want British colonies to decolonize, he agreed to the Atlantic Charter's decolonization provisions \"to get the Americans into the war\" with military aid on the side of the Allies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://history.state.gov/milestones/1937-1945/atlantic-conf|title=Milestones: 1937\u20131945 - Office of the Historian|website=history.state.gov|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> On January 1st 1942, the [[Declaration by United Nations|Declaration of the United Nations]] was signed by the [[Four Policemen|Big Four]] (the United States, United Kingdom, Soviet Union, and Republic of China), stipulating that the Atlantic Charter's pledges should be upheld. This became the basis of the [[Charter of the United Nations]] in 1945.\n\nDespite the weak protection of Hong Kong and agreements by the British to the Nine-Power Treaty, Atlantic Charter, and Declaration of the United Nations, at the end of the war, the British did not want to see Hong Kong handed over to the Republic of China, and moved quickly to [[Japanese occupation of Hong Kong#Post-war political stage|regain control]] of Hong Kong<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.endofempire.asia/0828-liberating-hong-kong-3/|title=Liberating Hong Kong|date=2015-08-28|website=End of Empire|language=en-US|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> in [[Liberation Day (Hong Kong)|1945]], preventing the unification of Hong Kong and the Republic of China (ROC). After the loss in the [[Chinese Civil War]] in 1949, the Koumintang-ruled Republic of China government, started by Sun Yat-sen, fled to Taiwan in [[Republic of China retreat to Taiwan|the Great Retreat]]. Shortly after, on 6 January 1950, the [[China\u2013United Kingdom relations|UK recognized]] the [[China|People's Republic of China]] (PRC) as the government of China due to economic interests, and blocked the Republic of China government from participating in the [[Treaty of San Francisco]] in 1951, which introduced the [[Political status of Taiwan|issue]] of which government Taiwan was to be surrendered to. Furthermore, in 1971, [[United Nations General Assembly Resolution 2758]] was supported by the British and passed, recognizing the PRC as the legitimate government of [[China and the United Nations|China in the UN]] rather than the Republic of China. Afterwards, the British and People's Republic of China began negotiations on the [[Handover of Hong Kong]], ultimately sealing Hong Kong's future with the PRC rather than the ROC.\n\nBoth during and after the Chinese Civil War, many people from Mainland China, including pro-Kuomintang refugees and former soldiers, fled to both [[1950s in Hong Kong|Hong Kong]] and Taiwan.  After the Civil War, the [[Pro-Taiwan camp (Hong Kong)|Pro-Taiwan camp]] was a major political force in Hong Kong, and many emigrants settled at [[Tiu Keng Leng|Rennie's Mill]], nicknamed \"Little Taiwan.\" On [[National Day of the Republic of China|Double Ten Day]], flags of the Republic of China were frequently seen in Hong Kong; the ordering of the removal<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/magazines/post-magazine/article/2025663/what-sparked-hong-kongs-double-tenth-riots|title=What sparked Hong Kong\u2019s Double Tenth riots|date=2016-10-07|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref> of one flag by a junior government official caused the [[Hong Kong 1956 riots|Hong Kong 1956 Riots]], when pro-Nationalists (called \"Rightists\") fought against [[Pro-Beijing camp (Hong Kong)|Pro-Communists]] (called \"Leftists\"). Though the flying of the Republic of China flag during Double Ten Day flag has decreased since the 1997 handover, it can still be seen to this day<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3032422/hong-kong-protesters-gather-mark-taiwans-celebration-108th|title=Hong Kong protesters gather to mark Taiwan\u2019s \u2018Double Tenth\u2019 holiday|date=2019-10-10|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/video/china/2114867/double-tenth-day-disappearing-flags-republic-china-hong-kong|title=Double Tenth day: the disappearing flags of the Republic of China in Hong Kong|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref> at places including [[Red House (Hong Kong)|Hung Lau]] in Tuen Mun, where an obelisk and bust of Sun Yat-sen are located. Hong Kong and Taiwan invested heavily in education and infrastructure after World War II, causing both economies to significantly improve and be part of the [[Four Asian Tigers]].\n\n== Official relations and politics ==\nSince 2010, the relationship between Hong Kong and the ROC is managed through the [[Hong Kong-Taiwan Economic and Cultural Co-operation and Promotion Council]] (ECCPC) and [[Taiwan-Hong Kong Economic and Cultural Co-operation Council]] (ECCC). Meanwhile, the [[Taipei Economic and Cultural Office in Hong Kong]] (TECO) is the representative office of the Republic of China in Hong Kong, while the [[Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office (Taiwan)|Hong Kong Economic, Trade and Cultural Office]] (HKETCO) is the representative office of Hong Kong in the Republic of China.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20031126025622/http://www.eslisland.com/guide/TaiwanEmbassiesabroad.htm Taiwanese Overseas 'Embassies' Abroad]</ref> In addition, the relations with Hong Kong is also conducted by the [[Mainland Affairs Council]], although not all regulations applicable to mainland China are automatically applied to those territories.\n\nIn recent times, both regions have been involved with each other politically. In 2014, students from Hong Kong supported Taiwan's [[Sunflower Student Movement]], and students from Taiwan supported the [[Umbrella Movement]] in Hong Kong.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/article/1595514/occupy-takes-seed-idea-sunflower-movement|title=Occupy takes seed of an idea from sunflower movement|date=2014-09-19|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> The [[Murder of Poon Hiu-wing|2018 murder by a Hong Kong citizen while in Taiwan]] caused the Hong Kong government to propose the [[2019 Hong Kong extradition bill|Hong Kong extradition bill]] in 2019, which would have allowed suspected criminals to be extradited to not just Taiwan, but Mainland China and Macau as well. This began massive [[2019 Hong Kong protests|protests]] in Hong Kong, with the government of Taiwan supporting the protesters, not wanting the proposal to become law.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1642413/why-taiwan-is-so-outspoken-on-hong-kongs-extradition-law/|title=Why Taiwan is the most outspoken critic of Hong Kong\u2019s extradition law|last=Steger|first=Isabella|website=Quartz|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> The government of Taiwan sees the extradition bill, now withdrawn, as an infringement of the [[one country, two systems]] principle, which has been the PRC's proposal for [[Chinese unification|unification]] with Taiwan. Tens of thousands of Taiwanese citizens marched in Taipei on 29 September 2019 in support of Hong Kong's pro-democracy movement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://focustaiwan.tw/news/acs/201909290011.aspx|title=Huge crowd rallies in Taipei to support Hong Kong democracy movement|website=focustaiwan.tw|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> Because of Taiwan's support of the protests, ROC flags have been frequently seen at protests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3032422/hong-kong-protesters-gather-mark-taiwans-celebration-108th|title=Hong Kong protesters gather to mark Taiwan\u2019s \u2018Double Tenth\u2019 holiday|date=2019-10-10|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> \n\n[[Joshua Wong]], a politician from Hong Kong, has also traveled to Taiwan to meet with the government to discuss the potential for Hong Kong protesters to seek political asylum in Taiwan<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/hong-kongs-joshua-wong-visits-taiwan-to-meet-with-ruling-party|title=Activist Joshua Wong urges Taiwanese to show support for Hong Kong|last=hermesauto|date=2019-09-03|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3025914/taiwans-refugee-bill-does-not-apply-hong-kong-protesters-now|title=Refugee bill does not apply to Hong Kong protesters for now, Taiwan says|date=2019-09-05|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref>. Keith Fong Chung-yin, president of the [[Hong Kong Baptist University]] Student Union, also echoed Joshua Wong's remarks about the lack of an asylum process in Taiwan and says the [[Democratic Progressive Party]] (DPP) has not enacted specific laws to help refugees<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/3832989|title=HK student leader says Taiwan\u2019s asylum ...|last=News|first=Taiwan|website=Taiwan News|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3041497/taiwanese-president-tsai-ing-wen-denies-using-hong-kong|title=Taiwanese president Tsai denies \u2018using\u2019 Hong Kong protests for election|date=2019-12-10|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>. Though [[Tsai Ing-wen]], the president of Taiwan, has regularly supported the protesters on social media and Article 18 of Taiwan's Laws and Regulations Regarding Hong Kong & Macao Affairs stipulates that \"Necessary assistance shall be provided to Hong Kong or Macau Residents whose safety and liberty are immediately threatened for political reasons<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mac.gov.tw/en/News_Content.aspx?n=2EA6ADFC159E7A0D&sms=8675D7361543DE23&s=52C62C35EEFEE30A&Create=1|title=Act Governing Relations with Hong Kong and Macau|date=2018-08-14|website=Mainland Affairs Council|language=en|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref>,\" the government of Taiwan has not created a process for political refugees yet<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thediplomat.com/2019/10/friends-from-hong-kong-taiwans-refugee-problem/|title=Friends from Hong Kong: Taiwan\u2019s Refugee Problem|website=thediplomat.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/11/26/781668197/some-hong-kong-protesters-are-seeking-refuge-in-taiwan-for-taiwan-its-complicate|title=Some Hong Kong Protesters Are Seeking Refuge In Taiwan. For Taiwan, It's Complicated|website=NPR.org|language=en|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref>.  [[Joseph Wu]], Taiwan's [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Republic of China)|Minister of Foreign Affairs]], has said that existing legislation to deal with refugees is sufficient<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/ap-interview-taiwan-may-help-111618072.html|title=AP Interview: Taiwan may help if Hong Kong violence expands|website=news.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>, even though a New York Times video<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/video/world/asia/100000006864895/hong-kong-protests-taiwan-secret-network.html|title=Protesters Are Fleeing Hong Kong. A Secret Network Is Helping Them.|last=Times|first=The New York|date=2019-12-08|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-12-11|language=English|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> has shown that some refugees from Hong Kong have entered Taiwan illegally, providing evidence that existing legislation is not sufficient. In response to the New York Times video, the [[Mainland Affairs Council]] warned protesters to not enter Taiwan illegally, and reiterated the statement that existing laws are sufficient<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1496709-20191209.htm?|title=HK protesters warned not to flee to Taiwan illegally - RTHK|website=news.rthk.hk|language=en-gb|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>, even though they only cover special cases, such as student, investment, and tourist visas. This lack of a formal asylum process means that refugees who do not qualify for student and investment visas enter Taiwan on 30-day tourist visas<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/08/world/asia/hong-kong-taiwan-protests.html|title=\u2018We Are Fleeing the Law\u2019: Hong Kong Protesters Escape to Taiwan|date=2019-12-08|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-12-11|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenation.com/article/taiwan-refugee-china-hongkong/|title=Why Taiwan Won\u2019t Welcome China\u2019s Dissidents|last=Aspinwall|first=Nick|date=2019-12-06|access-date=2020-01-05|language=en-US|issn=0027-8378}}</ref> and cannot legally work in Taiwan; despite this, some in Hong Kong have fled to Taiwan, including [[Causeway Bay Books]] founder [[Lam Wing-kee]]. In addition, Taiwan's Ministry of Education in November of 2019 announced that university students in Hong Kong would be allowed to attend lectures and continue their studies in Taiwan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3038634/taiwans-universities-open-doors-students-fleeing-hong-kong|title=Taiwan universities open doors to students fleeing Hong Kong|date=2019-11-21|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2019-11-28}}</ref> In contrast to the DPP's position of believing current laws are adequate, [[Han Kuo-yu]], the Kuomintang's candidate for the [[2020 Taiwan presidential election]], has said that he fully supports the passage of a refugee law to help asylum seekers from Hong Kong.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-protests-taiwan-idUSKBN1YG15K|title=Enact refugee law to help Hong Kong, Taiwan presidential hopeful says|date=2019-12-12|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-12-12|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Cultural ==\nCulturally, though the primary regional language of Hong Kong is [[Cantonese]] and the primary language of Taiwan is [[Mandarin Chinese|Mandarin]], both regions continue to use [[Traditional Chinese characters]], in contrast to [[Simplified Chinese characters]].\n\nAs a result of the war, no direct flights were allowed between Taiwan and Mainland China; thus many passengers transferred through Hong Kong until 2003, when the [[Cross-Strait charter]] was created. Travel between nationals of the two regions is popular; in 2018, there were approximately 1.7 million nationals of Taiwan who traveled to Hong Kong, the third-most destination after Japan (4.8 million) and Mainland China (4.1 million).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://admin.taiwan.net.tw/English/FileUploadCategoryListE003130.aspx?CategoryID=cde3e78b-82f0-4df9-8b88-c9c9e2cc08ac&appname=FileUploadCategoryListE003130|title=Tourism Statistics|last=\u4ea4\u901a\u90e8\u89c0\u5149\u5c40\u884c\u653f\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7db2|website=admin.taiwan.net.tw|language=en-us|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> These 1.7 million nationals represented Hong Kong's second-most inbound tourists, only after tourists from Mainland China.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tourism.gov.hk/english/statistics/statistics_perform.html|title=Tourism Commission - Tourism Performance|website=www.tourism.gov.hk|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> Non-stop flights are operated between [[Hong Kong International Airport|Hong Kong]] and Taipei ([[Taoyuan International Airport|Taoyuan]]), [[Taichung International Airport|Taichung]], [[Tainan Airport|Tainan]], and [[Kaohsiung International Airport|Kaohsiung]] airports.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Cross-Strait relations]]\n*[[Foreign relations of Hong Kong]]\n*[[Foreign relations of Taiwan]]\n*[[Pro-Taiwan camp (Hong Kong)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Foreign relations of Hong Kong}}\n{{Foreign relations of the Republic of China (Taiwan)}}\n{{Cross-Strait relations}}\n\n{{Hong Kong-stub}}\n{{Taiwan-poli-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Hong Kong\u2013Taiwan relations| ]]\n", "name_user": "MowerBreeze", "label": "safe", "comment": "Add flag of RoC in Hong Kong", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong%E2%80%93Taiwan_relations"}
{"title_page": "Buford and the Galloping Ghost", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| image = Buford Files.jpg\n| caption = [[File:The Galloping Ghost titlecard.jpg|200px]]\n| genre = [[Animation]] [[Mystery film|Mystery]]\n| director = [[Ray Patterson (animator)|Ray Patterson]]<br />[[Carl Urbano]]\n| voices = [[Frank Welker]]<br />[[Patricia Parris|Pat Parris]]<br />[[David Landsberg|Dave Landsburg]]<br />[[Marilyn Schreffler]]<br />[[Henry Corden]]<br />[[Harold Peary|Hal Peary]]\n| theme_music_composer = [[Hoyt Curtin]]\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| num_episodes = 13 (26 segments)\n| executive_producer = [[William Hanna]]<br />[[Joseph Barbera]]\n| producer = Art Scott\n| runtime = 30 minutes\n| company = [[Hanna-Barbera]]\n| distributor = [[Warner Bros. Television Distribution]]\n| network = [[NBC]]\n| audio_format = [[Monaural]]\n| first_aired = {{start date|1978|09|09}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|1979|09|01}}\n| related = ''[[Yogi's Space Race]]''\n}}\n'''''Buford and the Galloping Ghost''''' is an American [[Saturday-morning cartoon|animated television series]] and a [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of ''[[Yogi's Space Race]]'' produced by [[Hanna-Barbera|Hanna-Barbera Productions]] and broadcast on [[NBC]] from September 9, 1978, to September 1, 1979.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |pages=97-98 }}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nThe series featured the following two 11-minute segments:<ref name=\"green\">{{cite book|last=Green|first=Paul |title=Encyclopedia of Weird Westerns: Supernatural and Science Fiction Elements in Novels, Pulps, Comics, Films, Television, and Games|year=2009|publisher=McFarland|isbn=0-786-44390-1|page=47}}</ref>\n\n*'''The Buford Files''': Buford is a lazy bloodhound with a mournful bark and a sharp nose for solving mysteries who lives deep in Fenokee Swamp. He teams up with the teenage Boggs twins \u2013 '''Cindy Mae''' and '''Woody''' \u2013 and the trio solves confusing mysteries that baffle '''Sheriff Muletrain''' and his overeager, but dimwitted deputy '''Goofer McGee'''. Buford's abilities are expanded with ears that revolve like radar dishes, and his nose responds to clues like a Geiger counter. But Buford has two weaknesses: when the moon comes out, he howls his heart out, often at the most perilous moments and he also has a running feud with a karate-whacking raccoon.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Rovin |first1=Jeff |title=The Illustrated Encyclopedia of Cartoon Animals |date=1991 |publisher=Prentice Hall Press |isbn=0-13-275561-0 |accessdate=8 April 2020 |url=https://archive.org/details/illustratedencyc00rovi/page/38/mode/2up/ |page=38}}</ref>\n\n*'''The Galloping Ghost''': Nugget Nose is the short and feisty ghost of an Old West gold prospector who finds adventure riding his invisible horse. He is also a guardian to two teenage cowgirls, '''Wendy''' and '''Rita''', who work at the Fuddy Dude Ranch owned by grouchy, old '''Fenwick Fuddy'''. Whenever Fuddy threatens to fire the girls, Nugget makes himself invisible and becomes a helping friend. He is always battling Fuddy and takes delight in harassing him in odd and humorous ways. When the girls are in trouble, Wendy summons Nugget by rubbing on her special gold nugget necklace.\n\n''The Buford Files'' and ''The Galloping Ghost'' originally aired separately as segments on ''[[Yogi's Space Race]]'' from September 9, 1978, to January 27, 1979.<ref name=Woolery>{{cite book |last1=Woolery |first1=George W. |title=Children's Television: The First Thirty-Five Years, 1946-1981 |date=1983 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=0-8108-1557-5  |url=https://archive.org/details/childrenstelevis0000wool/page/50/mode/2up |accessdate=14 March 2020 |pages=50-51}}</ref> Following the cancellation of ''Yogi's Space Race'', both segments were repackaged and spun off in their own half-hour series from February 3 to September 1, 1979. The show has been rebroadcast on [[USA Cartoon Express]], [[Cartoon Network]] and [[Boomerang (TV network)|Boomerang]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Grossman|first=Gary H. |title=Saturday Morning TV|year=1988|publisher=Random House Value Publishing|isbn=0-517-64114-3|page=388}}</ref>\n\n==Voices==\n*[[Frank Welker]] \u2013 Buford, Nugget Nose\n*[[Patricia Parris|Pat Parris]] \u2013 Cindy Mae, Rita\n*[[David Landsberg|Dave Landsburg]] \u2013 Woody\n*[[Henry Corden]] \u2013 Sheriff Muletrain\n*Roger Petz \u2013 Goofer McGee\n*[[Marilyn Schreffler]] \u2013 Wendy\n*[[Harold Peary|Hal Peary]] \u2013 Fenwick Fuddy\n\n==Episodes==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#003cc8; width:20px\"| {{abbr|N\u00ba|Episode number}}\n! style=\"background:#003cc8\"| The Buford Files / The Galloping Ghost\n! style=\"background:#003cc8; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 1\n| Title = The Swamp Hermit / Phantom of the Horse Opera\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|9}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Swamp Hermit'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford visit their friend Jeb Crowley in Fenokee Swamp and soon discover he has been kidnapped by a pair of escaped convicts.\n* ''Phantom of the Horse Opera'': Wendy and Rita are star-struck with dreams of becoming movie stars when a Hollywood producer visits the Fuddy Dude Ranch.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 2\n| Title = The Vanishing Stallion / Too Many Crooks\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|16}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Vanishing Stallion'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford watch a stallion mysteriously disappear during the Fenokee annual steeplechase race.\n* ''Too Many Crooks'': A crook-on-the-loose seeks refuge at the Fuddy Dude Ranch; Wendy and Rita summon Nugget Nose to help save the day and capture the crook.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 3\n| Title = The Swamp Saucer / Sagebrush Sergeant\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|23}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Swamp Saucer'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford investigate when a mysterious UFO has been sighted in Fenokee Swamp and they get in contact with an astro-chimp.\n* ''Sagebrush Sergeant'': Mr. Fuddy's sister, a tough army sergeant, visits the ranch and starts Fuddy and the girls on a rigid schedule of exercise and work.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 4\n| Title = The Man with Orange Hair / Bad News Bear\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|30}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Man with Orange Hair'': At the Fenokee Sports Palace, Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford investigate when a pair of silver ice skates are stolen by a performer with orange hair.\n* ''Bad News Bear'': Nugget Nose and the girls try to prevent Mr. Fuddy and a safety inspector from discovering a grizzly bear hiding out at the Fuddy Dude Ranch.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 5\n| Title = The Demon of Ur / Robot Round-Up\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|7}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Demon of Ur'': Deputy Goofer fails to safeguard a demon statue of Ur, which disappears from a train bound from Tecusah to the Fenokee Community Center.\n* ''Robot Round-Up'': Wendy and Rita are worried of losing their jobs when Mr. Fuddy hires a robot to work at the Fuddy Dude Ranch.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 6\n| Title = The Missing Bank / Pests in the West\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|14}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Missing Bank'': Deputy Goofer delivers $10 million from Fenokee Bank to a bank in Culpepper in an armored car, but the bank president claims he never received the money.\n* ''Pests in the West'':\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 7\n| Title = Scare in the Air / Rock Star Nuggie\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|21}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''Scare in the Air'': At a Fenokee air show, Buford gets caught in a near-plane crashing accident and next comes an amphibious plane out of control and going missing.\n* ''Rock Star Nuggie'': Nugget Nose becomes jealous of Wendy and Rita's fawning over a visiting rock star and he begins causing trouble to scare him away.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 8\n| Title = Buford and the Beauty / Frontier Fortune Teller\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|28}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''Buford and the Beauty'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford go see a movie being filmed in Fenokee County starring a show dog named Duchess, who is kidnapped for ransom.\n* ''Frontier Fortune Teller'': Wendy and Rita seek Nugget Nose's help when a couple of thieves posing as phony fortune tellers plot to steal Mr. Fuddy's furniture.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 9\n| Title = Peril in the Park / I Want My Mummy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|11|4}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''Peril in the Park'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford visit the local amusement park to look for summer jobs, but the place is closing down because someone is sabotaging the rides.\n* ''I Want My Mummy'': At the Fuddy Dude Ranch costume party, Wendy is disguised as the mummy of Queen Tut-Tut, a rejuvenated ancient female Egyptian ruler.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 10\n| Title = The Magic Whammy / Mr. Sunshine's Eclipse\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|11|11}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Magic Whammy'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford attend the Great Zambini Magic Show while banks in Fenokee are mysteriously being robbed without any sign of a break-in.\n* ''Mr. Sunshine's Eclipse'': Wendy and Rita summon Nugget Nose to scare away Mr. Sunshine, an annoying TV prankster on vacation at the Fuddy Dude Ranch.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 11\n| Title = The Haunting of Swamp Manor / Klondike Kate\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|11|18}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Haunting of Swamp Manor'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford venture in the old Grimsley Mansion which is haunted by the ghost of Jedediah Grimsley, a Confederate general.\n* ''Klondike Kate'': Nugget Nose is reunited with Klondike Kate\u2014a ghost girlfriend from his past\u2014whom he had promised to marry if he struck gold.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 12\n| Title = The Case of the Missing Gator / A Ghost of a Chance\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|11|25}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Case of the Missing Gator'': Jeb Crowley's pet alligator, Gertrude, is missing and smugglers in the swamp are after some stolen diamonds.\n* ''A Ghost of a Chance'': A millionaire guest offers $1 million to prove that ghosts exist at the Fuddy Dude Ranch, so Mr. Fuddy goes to great lengths to try and capture Nugget Nose.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 13\n| Title = Don't Monkey with Buford / Elmo the Great\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|12|2}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''Don't Monkey with Buford'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford are invited to the circus by Duchess, whose diamond collar is stolen during the parade by a chimp.\n* ''Elmo the Great'': Wendy and Rita buy a horse named Elmo as a surprise birthday gift for Mr. Fuddy, but the troublesome horse becomes too much for Fuddy to handle.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n|}\n\n==Production==\n''Buford and the Galloping Ghost'' was animated at Filman, an animation studio in [[Madrid|Madrid, Spain]] (headed by Carlos Alfonso and Juan Pina) who did a lot of animation work for Hanna-Barbera between the early 1970s through the mid-1980s.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0078580|Buford and the Galloping Ghost}}\n* {{bcdb title|9751|Buford and the Galloping Ghost}}\n* [http://www.bcdb.com/cartoons/Hanna-Barbera_Studios/U-Z/Yogi_s_Space_Race/The_Buford_Files/index.html ''The Buford Files''] at [[The Big Cartoon DataBase]]\n* [http://www.bcdb.com/cartoons/Hanna-Barbera_Studios/U-Z/Yogi_s_Space_Race/The_Galloping_Ghost/index.html ''The Galloping Ghost''] at [[The Big Cartoon DataBase]]\n* [http://www.angelfire.com/tv2/buford/Buford1.htm ''The Buford Files''] at [[Angelfire]]\n\n{{Children's programming on NBC in the 1970s}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buford and the Galloping Ghost}}\n[[Category:1978 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1979 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:1970s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:American animated television programs featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated mystery television series]]\n[[Category:Animated western (genre) animation]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about dogs]]\n[[Category:Television series about ghosts]]\n[[Category:NBC original programming]]\n[[Category:American animated television spin-offs]]\n[[Category:Hanna-Barbera characters]]\n[[Category:Television series by Hanna-Barbera]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| image = Buford Files.jpg\n| caption = [[File:The Galloping Ghost titlecard.jpg|200px]]\n| genre = [[Animation]] [[Mystery film|Mystery]]\n| director = [[Ray Patterson (animator)|Ray Patterson]]<br />[[Carl Urbano]]\n| voices = [[Frank Welker]]<br />[[Patricia Parris|Pat Parris]]<br />[[David Landsberg|Dave Landsburg]]<br />[[Marilyn Schreffler]]<br />[[Henry Corden]]<br />[[Harold Peary|Hal Peary]]\n| theme_music_composer = [[Hoyt Curtin]]\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| num_episodes = 13 (26 segments)\n| executive_producer = [[William Hanna]]<br />[[Joseph Barbera]]\n| producer = Art Scott\n| runtime = 30 minutes\n| company = [[Hanna-Barbera]]\n| distributor = [[Warner Bros. Television Distribution]]\n| network = [[NBC]]\n| audio_format = [[Monaural]]\n| first_aired = {{start date|1978|09|09}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|1979|09|01}}\n| related = ''[[Yogi's Space Race]]''\n}}\n'''''Buford and the Galloping Ghost''''' is an American [[Saturday-morning cartoon|animated television series]] and a [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of ''[[Yogi's Space Race]]'' produced by [[Hanna-Barbera|Hanna-Barbera Productions]] which was broadcast on [[NBC]] from September 9, 1978, to September 1, 1979.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |pages=97-98 }}</ref> The series was composed of two 11-minute segments: ''The Buford Files'' and ''The Galloping Ghost''.<ref name=\"green\">{{cite book|last=Green|first=Paul |title=Encyclopedia of Weird Westerns: Supernatural and Science Fiction Elements in Novels, Pulps, Comics, Films, Television, and Games|year=2009|publisher=McFarland|isbn=0-786-44390-1|page=47}}</ref>\n\n''The Buford Files'' and ''The Galloping Ghost'' originally aired separately as segments on ''[[Yogi's Space Race]]'' from September 9, 1978, to January 27, 1979.<ref name=Woolery>{{cite book |last1=Woolery |first1=George W. |title=Children's Television: The First Thirty-Five Years, 1946-1981 |date=1983 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=0-8108-1557-5  |url=https://archive.org/details/childrenstelevis0000wool/page/50/mode/2up |accessdate=14 March 2020 |pages=50-51}}</ref> Following the cancellation of ''Yogi's Space Race'', both segments were repackaged and spun off in their own half-hour series from February 3 to September 1, 1979. The show has been rebroadcast on [[USA Cartoon Express]], [[Cartoon Network]] and [[Boomerang (TV network)|Boomerang]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Grossman|first=Gary H. |title=Saturday Morning TV|year=1988|publisher=Random House Value Publishing|isbn=0-517-64114-3|page=388}}</ref>\n\n==Characters==\n*'''Buford''' (voiced by [[Frank Welker]]): Buford is a lazy bloodhound with a mournful bark and a sharp nose for solving mysteries who lives deep in Fenokee Swamp.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Rovin |first1=Jeff |title=The Illustrated Encyclopedia of Cartoon Animals |date=1991 |publisher=Prentice Hall Press |isbn=0-13-275561-0 |accessdate=8 April 2020 |url=https://archive.org/details/illustratedencyc00rovi/page/38/mode/2up/ |page=38}}</ref> He teams up with the teenage Boggs twins \u2013 '''Cindy Mae''' and '''Woody''' (voiced by [[Patricia Parris|Pat Parris]] and [[David Landsberg|Dave Landsburg]]) \u2013 and the trio solves confusing mysteries that baffle '''Sheriff Muletrain''' (voiced by [[Henry Corden]]) and his overeager, but dimwitted deputy '''Goofer McGee''' (voiced by Roger Peltz). Buford's abilities are expanded with ears that revolve like radar dishes, and his nose responds to clues like a Geiger counter. But Buford has two weaknesses: when the moon comes out, he howls his heart out, often at the most perilous moments and he also has a running feud with a karate-whacking raccoon.\n\n*'''Nugget Nose''' (voiced by [[Frank Welker]]): Nugget Nose is the short and feisty ghost of an Old West gold prospector who finds adventure riding his invisible horse. He is also a guardian to two teenage cowgirls \u2013 '''Wendy''' and '''Rita''' (voiced by [[Marilyn Schreffler]] and [[Patricia Parris|Pat Parris]]) \u2013 who work at the Fuddy Dude Ranch owned by grouchy, old '''Fenwick Fuddy''' (voiced by [[Harold Peary|Hal Peary]]). Whenever Fuddy threatens to fire the girls, Nugget makes himself invisible and becomes a helping friend. He is always battling Fuddy and takes delight in harassing him in odd and humorous ways. When the girls are in trouble, Wendy summons Nugget by rubbing on her special gold nugget necklace.\n\nBuford, Nugget Nose, Wendy and Rita also participated in intergalactic racing competitions with [[Yogi Bear]], [[Huckleberry Hound]], [[Jabberjaw]] and other characters on the ''Yogi's Space Race'' segment (which was also spun-off into a separate half-hour). While Nugget Nose, Wendy and Rita race together as a trio, Buford's partner is Jabberjaw whose race ship contains a track on which Buford runs to increase speed.\n\n==Broadcast history==\n''The Buford Files'' and ''The Galloping Ghost'' segments were originally broadcast in these formats on [[NBC]]:\n* '''''Yogi's Space Race''''' (September 9, 1978 \u2013 October 28, 1978) (90 minutes)\n* '''''Yogi's Space Race''''' (November 4, 1978 \u2013 January 27, 1979) (60 minutes)\n* '''''Buford and the Galloping Ghost''''' (February 3, 1979 \u2013 September 1, 1979) (30 minutes)\n\nBroadcast schedules (all [[Eastern Time Zone|EDT]]):\n* September 9, 1978 \u2013 October 28, 1978, NBC Saturday 8:00-9:30 AM\n* November 4, 1978 \u2013 January 27, 1979, NBC Saturday 11:00 AM-12:00 PM\n* February 3, 1979 \u2013 September 1, 1979, NBC Saturday 12:00-12:30 PM\n\n==Episodes==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%; background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#003cc8; width:20px\"| {{abbr|N\u00ba|Episode number}}\n! style=\"background:#003cc8\"| The Buford Files / The Galloping Ghost\n! style=\"background:#003cc8; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 1\n| Title = The Swamp Hermit / Phantom of the Horse Opera\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|9}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Swamp Hermit'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford visit their friend Jeb Crowley in Fenokee Swamp and soon discover he has been kidnapped by a pair of escaped convicts.\n* ''Phantom of the Horse Opera'': Wendy and Rita are star-struck with dreams of becoming movie stars when a Hollywood producer visits the Fuddy Dude Ranch.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 2\n| Title = The Vanishing Stallion / Too Many Crooks\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|16}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Vanishing Stallion'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford watch a stallion mysteriously disappear during the Fenokee annual steeplechase race.\n* ''Too Many Crooks'': A crook-on-the-loose seeks refuge at the Fuddy Dude Ranch; Wendy and Rita summon Nugget Nose to help save the day and capture the crook.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 3\n| Title = The Swamp Saucer / Sagebrush Sergeant\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|23}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Swamp Saucer'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford investigate when a mysterious UFO has been sighted in Fenokee Swamp and they get in contact with an astro-chimp.\n* ''Sagebrush Sergeant'': Mr. Fuddy's sister, a tough army sergeant, visits the ranch and starts Fuddy and the girls on a rigid schedule of exercise and work.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 4\n| Title = The Man with Orange Hair / Bad News Bear\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|9|30}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Man with Orange Hair'': At the Fenokee Sports Palace, Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford investigate when a pair of silver ice skates are stolen by a performer with orange hair.\n* ''Bad News Bear'': Nugget Nose and the girls try to prevent Mr. Fuddy and a safety inspector from discovering a grizzly bear hiding out at the Fuddy Dude Ranch.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 5\n| Title = The Demon of Ur / Robot Round-Up\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|7}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Demon of Ur'': Deputy Goofer fails to safeguard a demon statue of Ur, which disappears from a train bound from Tecusah to the Fenokee Community Center.\n* ''Robot Round-Up'': Wendy and Rita are worried of losing their jobs when Mr. Fuddy hires a robot to work at the Fuddy Dude Ranch.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 6\n| Title = The Missing Bank / Pests in the West\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|14}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Missing Bank'': Deputy Goofer delivers $10 million from Fenokee Bank to a bank in Culpepper in an armored car, but the bank president claims he never received the money.\n* ''Pests in the West'':\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 7\n| Title = Scare in the Air / Rock Star Nuggie\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|21}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''Scare in the Air'': At a Fenokee air show, Buford gets caught in a near-plane crashing accident and next comes an amphibious plane out of control and going missing.\n* ''Rock Star Nuggie'': Nugget Nose becomes jealous of Wendy and Rita's fawning over a visiting rock star and he begins causing trouble to scare him away.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 8\n| Title = Buford and the Beauty / Frontier Fortune Teller\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|10|28}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''Buford and the Beauty'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford go see a movie being filmed in Fenokee County starring a show dog named Duchess, who is kidnapped for ransom.\n* ''Frontier Fortune Teller'': Wendy and Rita seek Nugget Nose's help when a couple of thieves posing as phony fortune tellers plot to steal Mr. Fuddy's furniture.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 9\n| Title = Peril in the Park / I Want My Mummy\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|11|4}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''Peril in the Park'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford visit the local amusement park to look for summer jobs, but the place is closing down because someone is sabotaging the rides.\n* ''I Want My Mummy'': At the Fuddy Dude Ranch costume party, Wendy is disguised as the mummy of Queen Tut-Tut, a rejuvenated ancient female Egyptian ruler.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 10\n| Title = The Magic Whammy / Mr. Sunshine's Eclipse\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|11|11}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Magic Whammy'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford attend the Great Zambini Magic Show while banks in Fenokee are mysteriously being robbed without any sign of a break-in.\n* ''Mr. Sunshine's Eclipse'': Wendy and Rita summon Nugget Nose to scare away Mr. Sunshine, an annoying TV prankster on vacation at the Fuddy Dude Ranch.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 11\n| Title = The Haunting of Swamp Manor / Klondike Kate\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|11|18}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Haunting of Swamp Manor'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford venture in the old Grimsley Mansion which is haunted by the ghost of Jedediah Grimsley, a Confederate general.\n* ''Klondike Kate'': Nugget Nose is reunited with Klondike Kate\u2014a ghost girlfriend from his past\u2014whom he had promised to marry if he struck gold.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 12\n| Title = The Case of the Missing Gator / A Ghost of a Chance\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|11|25}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''The Case of the Missing Gator'': Jeb Crowley's pet alligator, Gertrude, is missing and smugglers in the swamp are after some stolen diamonds.\n* ''A Ghost of a Chance'': A millionaire guest offers $1 million to prove that ghosts exist at the Fuddy Dude Ranch, so Mr. Fuddy goes to great lengths to try and capture Nugget Nose.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber = 13\n| Title = Don't Monkey with Buford / Elmo the Great\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|1978|12|2}}\n| ShortSummary = * ''Don't Monkey with Buford'': Woody, Cindy Mae and Buford are invited to the circus by Duchess, whose diamond collar is stolen during the parade by a chimp.\n* ''Elmo the Great'': Wendy and Rita buy a horse named Elmo as a surprise birthday gift for Mr. Fuddy, but the troublesome horse becomes too much for Fuddy to handle.\n| LineColor = 003cc8\n}}\n|}\n\n==Production==\n''Buford and the Galloping Ghost'' was animated at Filman, an animation studio in [[Madrid|Madrid, Spain]] (headed by Carlos Alfonso and Juan Pina) who did a lot of animation work for Hanna-Barbera between the early 1970s through the mid-1980s.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0078580|Buford and the Galloping Ghost}}\n* {{bcdb title|9751|Buford and the Galloping Ghost}}\n* [http://www.bcdb.com/cartoons/Hanna-Barbera_Studios/U-Z/Yogi_s_Space_Race/The_Buford_Files/index.html ''The Buford Files''] at [[The Big Cartoon DataBase]]\n* [http://www.bcdb.com/cartoons/Hanna-Barbera_Studios/U-Z/Yogi_s_Space_Race/The_Galloping_Ghost/index.html ''The Galloping Ghost''] at [[The Big Cartoon DataBase]]\n* [http://www.angelfire.com/tv2/buford/Buford1.htm ''The Buford Files''] at [[Angelfire]]\n\n{{Children's programming on NBC in the 1970s}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buford and the Galloping Ghost}}\n[[Category:1978 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1979 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:1970s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:American animated television programs featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated mystery television series]]\n[[Category:Animated western (genre) animation]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about dogs]]\n[[Category:Television series about ghosts]]\n[[Category:NBC original programming]]\n[[Category:American animated television spin-offs]]\n[[Category:Hanna-Barbera characters]]\n[[Category:Television series by Hanna-Barbera]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buford_and_the_Galloping_Ghost"}
{"title_page": "Maynila (TV program)", "text_new": "{{short description|Philippine television show}}\n{{refimprove|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Maynila\n| show_name_2 = {{plain list|\n* ''Maynila: Larawan ng Bansa'' (2008\u20132009)\n* ''Maynila: Ito ang Kwento Mo'' (2014\u20132017)\n* ''Maynila: Kwento. Buhay. Tagumpay.'' (since 2017)}}\n| image = Maynila title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card since 2017\n| genre = {{plain list|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Romance film|Romance]]}}\n| company = Maynilad Golden Productions Inc.\n| writer = {{plainlist|\n* Sara San Luis\n* Rouel Alciraz\n* Theresa Guevarra}}\n| director = G. Phil M. Noble \n| presenter = [[Lito Atienza]]\n| opentheme = {{plain list|\n* \"Mahal kong Maynila\" by Cacai Bautista and Vince De Jesus (2002\u20132008; 2010\u20132015; since 2020)\n* \"Maynila\" by Noel Cabangon (2015\u20132020)}}\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| list_episodes = List of Maynila episodes\n| executive_producer = {{plain list|\n* Alessandra A. Beltran\n* Lani Atienza}}\n| location = [[Manila]], Philippines\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| runtime = {{plainlist|\n* 30 minutes (1998\u20132002)\n* 60 minutes (since 2002)}}\n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired = {{start date|1998|11|23}}\n| last_aired = present\n}}\n\n'''''Maynila''''' ({{translation|Manila}}) is a [[Philippine television drama]] romance anthology show broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. Hosted by [[Lito Atienza]], it premiered on November 23, 1998. The show originally aired on weekday afternoons, and was later moved to Saturday mornings in 2002.\n\n==Overview==\nPresented as an anthology, ''Maynila'' is a series of inspiring stories of people with everyday challenges that affect Manila residents.<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/pg/MaynilaTV/about/?ref=page_internal About Maynila TV]</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{main|List of Maynila episodes}}\n\n==Hosts==\n*[[Lito Atienza]] - former [[Department of Environment and Natural Resources (Philippines)|DENR]] Secretary, Manila mayor & current BUHAY Partylist representative.\n*[[Ali Atienza]] - sit-in host while his father was running for Mayor of Manila in 2010.\n*Lei Atienza-Valdepenas (2004; 2016-present)\n\n==Production==\nPrincipal photography was halted in March 2020 due to the enhanced community quarantine caused by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.interaksyon.com/trends-spotlights/2020/03/17/164497/abscbn-gma-top-rating-shows-comeback-covid19-quarantine/ |title=Top-rating ABS-CBN, GMA shows make TV comeback as quarantine halts regular programs |author=Adel, Rosette |date=March 17, 2020 |accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n*Nominated, Best Drama Anthology - PMPC Star Awards For TV (1999-2018)\n*Nominated, Best Drama Series - Catholic Mass Media Awards (1999-2017)\n*Anak TV Seal Award - 2006\n*Certificate of Recognition -  The First Stars Night Out by Artist Handlers Group 2012\n*Winner, Best New Male TV Personality For Ruru Madrid \"Maynila: Faith In Love\" - PMPC Star Awards For TV 2013\n*Special Award Winner, Longest Running Drama Anthology - PMPC Star Awards For TV 2017\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3742304}}\n\n{{GMA Network (current and upcoming original programming)}}\n[[Category:GMA Network shows]]\n[[Category:Philippine anthology television series]]\n[[Category:1998 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Manila]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Philippine television show}}\n{{refimprove|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Maynila\n| show_name_2 = {{plain list|\n* ''Maynila: Larawan ng Bansa'' (2008\u20132009)\n* ''Maynila: Ito ang Kwento Mo'' (2014\u20132017)\n* ''Maynila: Kwento. Buhay. Tagumpay.'' (since 2017)}}\n| image = Maynila title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card since 2017\n| genre = {{plain list|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Romance film|Romance]]}}\n| company = Maynilad Golden Productions Inc.\n| writer = {{plainlist|\n* Sara San Luis\n* Rouel Alciraz\n* Theresa Guevarra}}\n| director = G. Phil M. Noble \n| presenter = [[Lito Atienza]]\n| opentheme = {{plain list|\n* \"Mahal kong Maynila\" by Cacai Bautista and Vince De Jesus (2002\u20132008; 2010\u20132015; since 2020)\n* \"Maynila\" by Noel Cabangon (2015\u20132020)}}\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| list_episodes = List of Maynila episodes\n| executive_producer = {{plain list|\n* Alessandra A. Beltran\n* Lani Atienza}}\n| location = [[Manila]], Philippines\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| runtime = {{plainlist|\n* 30 minutes (1999\u20132002)\n* 60 minutes (since 2002)}}\n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired = {{start date|1999|12|13}}\n| last_aired = present\n}}\n\n'''''Maynila''''' ({{translation|Manila}}) is a [[Philippine television drama]] romance anthology show broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. Hosted by [[Lito Atienza]], it premiered on December 13, 1999. The show originally aired on weekday afternoons, and was later moved to Saturday mornings in 2002.\n\n==Overview==\nPresented as an anthology, ''Maynila'' is a series of inspiring stories of people with everyday challenges that affect Manila residents.<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/pg/MaynilaTV/about/?ref=page_internal About Maynila TV]</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{main|List of Maynila episodes}}\n\n==Hosts==\n*[[Lito Atienza]] - former [[Department of Environment and Natural Resources (Philippines)|DENR]] Secretary, Manila mayor & current BUHAY Partylist representative.\n*[[Ali Atienza]] - sit-in host while his father was running for Mayor of Manila in 2010.\n*Lei Atienza-Valdepenas (2004; 2016-present)\n\n==Production==\nMaynila was halted in April 2020 due to the enhanced community quarantine caused by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.interaksyon.com/trends-spotlights/2020/03/17/164497/abscbn-gma-top-rating-shows-comeback-covid19-quarantine/ |title=Top-rating ABS-CBN, GMA shows make TV comeback as quarantine halts regular programs |author=Adel, Rosette |date=March 17, 2020 |accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n*Nominated, Best Drama Anthology - PMPC Star Awards For TV (2000-2018)\n*Nominated, Best Drama Series - Catholic Mass Media Awards (2000-2017)\n*Anak TV Seal Award - 2006\n*Certificate of Recognition -  The First Stars Night Out by Artist Handlers Group 2012\n*Winner, Best New Male TV Personality For Ruru Madrid \"Maynila: Faith In Love\" - PMPC Star Awards For TV 2013\n*Special Award Winner, Longest Running Drama Anthology - PMPC Star Awards For TV 2017\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3742304}}\n\n{{GMA Network (current and upcoming original programming)}}\n[[Category:GMA Network shows]]\n[[Category:Philippine anthology television series]]\n[[Category:1998 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Manila]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Hotwiki", "label": "safe", "comment": "Restored", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maynila_(TV_program)"}
{"title_page": "European Commodity Clearing", "text_new": "{{Infobox company  \n| name = European Commodity Clearing AG\n| logo = ECC Logo.png\n| foundation =  2006   \n| location =   Leipzig, Germany   \n| employees =      <!-- Approx number of employees -->\n| products =     Clearing and settlement services for energy and other commodities  \n| key_people = Peter Reitz (CEO), Dr. G\u00f6tz Dittrich (COO), Dr. Thomas Siegl (CRO), Jens Rick (CIO)\n| homepage=        [http://www.ecc.de/ www.ecc.de]    \n}}\n\n'''European Commodity Clearing''' AG (ECC) is the leading clearing house for energy and commodity products in Europe and the central clearing house for the Global Commodity Exchange, EEX Group. ECC assumes the counterparty risk and guarantees the physical and financial settlement of transactions, providing security and cross-margining benefits for its customers. As part of EEX Group, ECC provides clearing services for EEX, EEX Asia and EPEX SPOT with additional services provided to Power Exchange Central Europe (PXE). In addition, ECC also provides clearing services for the partner exchanges HUPX, HUDEX, NOREXECO, SEEPEX and SEMOpx.\n\n== Foundation ==\nECC was established as a subsidiary of the European Energy Exchange (EEX) in 2006. In this context, EEX transferred its clearing activities to ECC.  The aim has been to provide clearing services for partner exchanges as well. As a first step in this direction, on 5 July 2006, the European Energy Exchange AG (EEX) and the Amsterdam-based European Energy Derivatives Exchange N.V. (ENDEX) announced they would cooperate in the settlement of energy trading transactions.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/252, |title=Press Release, 07/04/2006 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416180315/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/252, |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nThis cooperation agreement constituted ECC's first step towards a clearing house working for several exchanges. ECC acts as central counterparty for the exchanges of EEX group and further partner exchange. Currently, 10 partner exchange use the clearing and settlement services of ECC. <ref>[http://www.ecc.de/ecc-en/about-ecc/partners-products/partner-exchanges, ECC website]</ref>\n\n== Services ==\nCurrently, ECC provides clearing services for the Partner Exchanges EEX Asia, European Energy Exchange (EEX), EPEX SPOT, Hungarian Derivative Energy Exchange (HUDEX), Hungarian Power Exchange (HUPX), Norexeco, Powernext, POWER EXCHANGE CENTRAL EUROPE (PXE), SEEPEX and SEMOpx.\n\nOverall, ECC provides clearing and settlement services for the following products:<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/partners-products/products |title=Products of ECC |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416175704/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/partners-products/products |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Power (Germany, France, Austria, Switzerland, Belgium, the Netherlands, Great Britain, Hungary)\n* Natural Gas (Germany, France, the Netherlands, Austria)\n* Emission allowances (EUA, CER, EUAA)\n*Pulp (NBSK & BHKP)\n\n== Expansion of the product offerings ==\n* November 2008: ECC now provides clearing and settlement for natural gas contracts traded on the French exchange Powernext SA.\n* April 2009: The clearing and settlement of all French power spot and derivatives contracts within the framework of the cooperation between EEX and Powernext is now assumed by ECC. \n* October 2009: ECC assumes clearing and settlement for UK Power Futures.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/5671 |title=Press Release, 10/02/2009 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416175710/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/5671 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* December 2009: ECC assumes clearing and settlement services for the new gas market in Austria. The trade is executed on the stock exchange systems of the Vienna Stock Exchange, delivery point is the [[Central European Gas Hub]] (CEGH).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/5267 |title=Press Release, 06/25/2009 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416205828/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/5267 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* July 2010: ECC also acts as a clearing house for the newly built [[HUPX Hungarian Power Exchange]] and takes over the clearing and settlement of transactions concluded on HUPX electricity spot market in the framework of this cooperation.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/7327 |title=Press Release, 07/20/2010 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416174838/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/7327 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* December 2010: Clearing is extended by derivative market products.\n* July 2011: ECC takes over the clearing for HUPX electricity futures.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/11420 |title=Press Release, 07/19/2011 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416175708/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/11420 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* February 2013: EEX group continues expanding its Trade Registration Services to offer more products that are not traded on the EEX or ECC partner exchanges.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/17124 |title=Press Release, 02/14/2013 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416174835/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/17124 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* June 2013: EEX offers trading in Guarantees of Origin (GoOs). These certificates prove that one megawatt hour of electricity was generated from renewable energy sources. ECC takes over clearing and settlement of the trades.\n* September 2013: ECC assumes clearing and settlement of all trades completed at the Prague-based Power Exchange Central Europe (PXE).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/18332 |title=Press Release, 09/02/2013 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416205826/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/18332 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* December 2013: ECC and the Norwegian NOREXECO AS have agreed to cooperate in commodity trading, clearing and settlement and have concluded a cooperation agreement for that purpose.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/18815 |title=Press Release, 12/11/2013 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416175316/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/18815 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* December 2013: EEX has become the majority shareholder of the Singaporean Futures Exchange Clear Trade Exchange (CLTX). The aim is to build a new global supply of raw materials. The CLTX supplements the existing products of the EEX with products such as freight, iron ore, fuel oil and fertilizers.\n\n== Resources ==\n*[http://www.ecc.de ECC Website]\n\nPartner exchanges:\n*[http://www.eex.com EEX Website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071012135006/http://powernext.fr/ Powernext Website]\n*<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.norexeco.com/|title=NOREXECO Website|website=www.norexeco.com|access-date=2018-12-06}}</ref>\n*[http://www.epexspot.com EPEX Spot Website]\n*[http://www.ceghex.com CEGH Website]\n*[http://www.hupx.hu HUPX Website]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n[[category:Companies_based_in_Leipzig]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company  \n| name = European Commodity Clearing AG\n| logo = ECC Logo.png\n| foundation =  2006   \n| location =   Leipzig, Germany   \n| employees =      <!-- Approx number of employees -->\n| products =     Clearing and settlement services for energy and other commodities  \n| key_people = Peter Reitz (CEO), Dr. G\u00f6tz Dittrich (COO), Dr. Thomas Siegl (CRO), Jens Rick (CIO)\n| homepage=        [http://www.ecc.de/ www.ecc.de]    \n}}\n\n'''European Commodity Clearing''' AG (ECC) is a [[Clearing house (finance)|clearing house]] which provides clearing and settlement services for energy and other commodities traded on an exchange or via Trade Registration. The ECC AG is a subsidiary of the [[European Energy Exchange]] AG (EEX).\n\n== Foundation ==\nECC was established as a subsidiary of the European Energy Exchange (EEX) in 2006. In this context, EEX transferred its clearing activities to ECC.  The aim has been to provide clearing services for partner exchanges as well. As a first step in this direction, on 5 July 2006, the European Energy Exchange AG (EEX) and the Amsterdam-based European Energy Derivatives Exchange N.V. (ENDEX) announced they would cooperate in the settlement of energy trading transactions.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/252, |title=Press Release, 07/04/2006 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416180315/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/252, |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nThis cooperation agreement constituted ECC's first step towards a clearing house working for several exchanges. ECC acts as central counterparty for the exchanges of EEX group and further partner exchange. Currently, 10 partner exchange use the clearing and settlement services of ECC. <ref>[http://www.ecc.de/ecc-en/about-ecc/partners-products/partner-exchanges, ECC website]</ref>\n\n== Services ==\nCurrently, ECC provides clearing services for the Partner Exchanges EEX Asia, European Energy Exchange (EEX), EPEX SPOT, Hungarian Derivative Energy Exchange (HUDEX), Hungarian Power Exchange (HUPX), Norexeco, Powernext, POWER EXCHANGE CENTRAL EUROPE (PXE), SEEPEX and SEMOpx.\n\nOverall, ECC provides clearing and settlement services for the following products:<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/partners-products/products |title=Products of ECC |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416175704/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/partners-products/products |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Power (Germany, France, Austria, Switzerland, Belgium, the Netherlands, Great Britain, Hungary)\n* Natural Gas (Germany, France, the Netherlands, Austria)\n* Emission allowances (EUA, CER, EUAA)\n*Pulp (NBSK & BHKP)\n\n== Expansion of the product offerings ==\n* November 2008: ECC now provides clearing and settlement for natural gas contracts traded on the French exchange Powernext SA.\n* April 2009: The clearing and settlement of all French power spot and derivatives contracts within the framework of the cooperation between EEX and Powernext is now assumed by ECC. \n* October 2009: ECC assumes clearing and settlement for UK Power Futures.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/5671 |title=Press Release, 10/02/2009 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416175710/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/5671 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* December 2009: ECC assumes clearing and settlement services for the new gas market in Austria. The trade is executed on the stock exchange systems of the Vienna Stock Exchange, delivery point is the [[Central European Gas Hub]] (CEGH).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/5267 |title=Press Release, 06/25/2009 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416205828/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/5267 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* July 2010: ECC also acts as a clearing house for the newly built [[HUPX Hungarian Power Exchange]] and takes over the clearing and settlement of transactions concluded on HUPX electricity spot market in the framework of this cooperation.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/7327 |title=Press Release, 07/20/2010 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416174838/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/7327 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* December 2010: Clearing is extended by derivative market products.\n* July 2011: ECC takes over the clearing for HUPX electricity futures.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/11420 |title=Press Release, 07/19/2011 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416175708/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/11420 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* February 2013: EEX group continues expanding its Trade Registration Services to offer more products that are not traded on the EEX or ECC partner exchanges.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/17124 |title=Press Release, 02/14/2013 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416174835/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/17124 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* June 2013: EEX offers trading in Guarantees of Origin (GoOs). These certificates prove that one megawatt hour of electricity was generated from renewable energy sources. ECC takes over clearing and settlement of the trades.\n* September 2013: ECC assumes clearing and settlement of all trades completed at the Prague-based Power Exchange Central Europe (PXE).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/18332 |title=Press Release, 09/02/2013 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416205826/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/18332 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* December 2013: ECC and the Norwegian NOREXECO AS have agreed to cooperate in commodity trading, clearing and settlement and have concluded a cooperation agreement for that purpose.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/18815 |title=Press Release, 12/11/2013 |access-date=2014-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416175316/http://www.ecc.de/en/about-ecc/news/press-releases/press-releases-detail/press/18815 |archive-date=2014-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* December 2013: EEX has become the majority shareholder of the Singaporean Futures Exchange Clear Trade Exchange (CLTX). The aim is to build a new global supply of raw materials. The CLTX supplements the existing products of the EEX with products such as freight, iron ore, fuel oil and fertilizers.\n\n== Resources ==\n*[http://www.ecc.de ECC Website]\n\nPartner exchanges:\n*[http://www.eex.com EEX Website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071012135006/http://powernext.fr/ Powernext Website]\n*<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.norexeco.com/|title=NOREXECO Website|website=www.norexeco.com|access-date=2018-12-06}}</ref>\n*[http://www.epexspot.com EPEX Spot Website]\n*[http://www.ceghex.com CEGH Website]\n*[http://www.hupx.hu HUPX Website]\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n[[category:Companies_based_in_Leipzig]]\n", "name_user": "Ursula Goetze", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Commodity_Clearing"}
{"title_page": "Frederick Fleet", "text_new": "{{short description|British sailor}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2012}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Frederick Fleet\n| image = FrederickFleet.April1912.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| caption = Fleet in 1912\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|1887|10|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Liverpool]], UK\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|1965|1|10|1887|10|15|df=y}}\n| death_place = [[Southampton]], UK \n| death_cause = [[Suicide by hanging]]\n| birth_name = \n| occupation  = [[Sailor]], [[Crewman]]lookout\n\n| nationality = [[United Kingdom|British]]\n}}\n\n'''Frederick Fleet''' (15 October 1887&nbsp;\u2013 10 January 1965) was a British [[sailor]], [[crewman]] and survivor of the [[Sinking of the RMS Titanic|sinking of the]] {{RMS|Titanic}} after it struck an [[iceberg]] on 14 April 1912.<ref>Fleet was second-in-charge aboard lifeboat #6</ref> Along with fellow lookout [[Reginald Lee]], on duty, aboard the ''Titanic'' when the ship struck the iceberg, contrary to popular belief, Fleet was most likely not the man who spotted the Iceberg. In the enquiry, Fleet stated that the ship began turning immediatly after phoning the bridge about the Iceberg. This leads historians to believe First Officer 'William McMaster Murdoch' was the man to spot the berg. The phone call to the Bridge (answered by 6th Officer Moody) was where Fleet's famous \"Iceberg dead ahead!\" originated.  <ref name=\"USInquiry\">[http://www.titanicinquiry.org/USInq/AmInq04Fleet01.php United States Senate Inquiry Day 4], Testimony of Frederick Fleet.</ref>\n\nFleet testified at the subsequent inquiries into the sinking that, had he and Lee been issued with [[binoculars]]: \"We could have seen it (the iceberg) a bit sooner.\" When asked how much sooner, he responded, \"Well, enough to get out of the way.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.titanicinquiry.org/USInq2/AmInq04Fleet02.php|title=TIP - United States Senate Inquiry - Day 4 - Testimony of Frederick Fleet, cont.|website=www.titanicinquiry.org}}</ref> In later life, Fleet suffered severe [[Major depressive disorder|depression]] and as a result committed suicide by hanging in January 1965.\n\n== Biography ==\n\n=== Early life and sea career ===\nFleet was born in Liverpool on 15 October 1887. He never knew his father, and his mother abandoned him and fled with a boyfriend to [[Springfield, Massachusetts]], in the [[United States]] never to be seen or heard from again.<ref name=\"bookdummies\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 118\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> Frederick was raised by a succession of foster families and distant relatives. In 1903 he went to sea as a deck boy, working his way up to [[able seaman]].<ref name=\"nationalarchivesuk\">[http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/titanic/stories/frederick-fleet.htm Stories from The Titanic], National Archives UK.</ref>\n\nBefore joining the [[Crew of the RMS Titanic|crew of the RMS ''Titanic'']] he had sailed for over four years as a [[lookout]] in the [[RMS Oceanic (1899)|RMS ''Oceanic'']].<ref name=\"nationalarchivesuk\"/> As a seaman, Fleet earned five pounds per month plus an extra 5 [[shilling]]s for lookout duty.<ref name=\"nationalarchivesuk\"/> And it was as a lookout that Fleet joined the ''Titanic'' in April 1912, along with five other watchmen.<ref name=\"nationalarchivesuk\"/>\n\n===R.M.S. ''Titanic''===\n[[Image:Titanic Eisberg.jpg|thumb|right|250px|This iceberg was pictured in the morning of 15 April 1912 and is thought to be the one that the ''Titanic'' had struck.]][[Image:Titanic Bridge and Crow's Nest.png|thumb|left|150px|The crow's nest from which Fleet and Lee spotted the iceberg can be seen in the picture.]]\nFleet boarded the ''Titanic'' in [[Southampton]] on 10 April 1912. The ship made two stops, first in [[Cherbourg, France|Cherbourg]], France and [[Queenstown, Ireland|Queenstown]], in Ireland. The lookouts, six in total, made two-hour shifts due to extreme cold in the crow's nest.<ref name=\"bookseas\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Golden | first1 = Frank\n| last2 = Tipton | first2 = Michael\n| title = Essentials of Sea Survival\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Human Kinetics Pub Inc]]\n| page = 12\n| date = June 2002\n| isbn = 978-0-7360-0215-8}}</ref> The trip was uneventful until the night of 14 April 1912. At 22:00 (10&nbsp;p.m.) that night, Fleet and his fellow lookout [[Reginald Lee]] replaced [[George Symons (RMS Titanic)|George Symons]] and Archie Jewell at the nest.<ref name=\"bookrupert\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Matthews | first1 = Rupert\n| title = Titanic: The Tragic Story of the Ill-fated Ocean Liner\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Arcturus Publishing]]\n| pages = \n| date = March 2011\n| isbn = 1-84837-763-0}}</ref> They passed on the order given earlier to them by second officer [[Charles Lightoller]] to watch out for small ice.<ref name=\"bookdummies1\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 86\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> The night was calm and moonless, which made it difficult to spot the [[iceberg]]s due to the lack of waves breaking against the base of the iceberg and [[Reflection (physics)|reflection]].<ref name=\"Everything Was Against Us\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Angel | first1 = Simon\n| title = The Titanic - \"Everything Was Against Us\"\n| location = \n| publisher = [[CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform]]\n| page = 53\n| date = April 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-4751-2793-5}}</ref> Furthermore, despite Fleet and his fellow lookouts having repeatedly requested being provided with binoculars,<ref>[https://historicsouthampton.wordpress.com/2016/09/18/frederick-fleet/ ''historicsouthampton.wordpress.com/'']</ref><ref>[https://www.encyclopedia-titanica.org/defending-fleet-and-lee.html ''encyclopedia-titanica.org'']</ref> they were not available for the lookouts. It is sometimes attributed to the last-minute change in the hierarchy of the ship when officer [[David Blair (mariner)|David Blair]] was replaced by [[Henry Tingle Wilde]], without Blair mentioning where the binoculars had been located. It has been also mentioned that Blair accidentally took the keys of the cabinet containing the binoculars with him.<ref name=\"blair\">[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-478269/Is-man-sank-Titanic-walking-vital-locker-key.html Is this the man who sank the Titanic by walking off with vital locker key?], [[Daily Mail]].</ref> Despite both inquiries into the disaster, nothing clarified why the lookouts were not provided with binoculars, though there are many explanations such as one that the [[White Star Line]] steamers' lookouts did not particularly use them.<ref name=\"ripples\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Maltin | first1 = Tim\n| last2 = Aston | first2 = Eloise\n| title = 101 Things You Thought You Knew about the Titanic - But Didn't!\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Penguin Books]]\n| page = 33\n| date = November 2011\n| isbn = 978-0-14-311909-8}}</ref> Besides, some experts have said that even using binoculars, neither Fleet nor Lee could have spotted the iceberg any sooner given the conditions of the night.<ref name=\"nbc\">[http://cosmiclog.nbcnews.com/_news/2012/04/01/10970732-10-causes-of-the-titanic-tragedy 10 causes of the Titanic tragedy], NBC news.</ref>\n\nAt 23:39 (11:39&nbsp;p.m.), Fleet first spotted the iceberg and rang the nest's bell three times to warn the bridge of something ahead. Then, using the nest's telephone, he contacted the bridge. It was answered only a few seconds later by sixth officer [[James Paul Moody]], who asked Fleet immediately, \"What did you see?\" He pronounced the infamous \"Iceberg! Right Ahead!\" warning to Moody. Moody acknowledged Fleet's warning, and immediately notified first officer [[William McMaster Murdoch]]; in charge of the bridge.<ref name=\"bookdummies2\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 304\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> After the collision, Fleet and Lee remained on duty for twenty more minutes.<ref name=\"herald\">[http://www.herald-dispatch.com/news/putnam/x1596692627/Fred-Fleet-did-his-duty-on-Titanic-now-resting-in-peace Fred Fleet did his duty on Titanic, now resting in peace], Herald Dispatch.</ref>\n[[Image:Titanicboat6.gif|thumb|right|150px|Lifeboat 6 approaching the [[RMS Carpathia|RMS ''Carpathia'']]; Fleet can be seen trying to tie the boat to the [[davit]]s of the ship.]]\nAt 00:00 (12&nbsp;a.m.), Fleet and Lee were relieved by Alfred Frank Evans and George Hogg.<ref name=\"bookinquiries\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Kuntz | first1 = Tom\n| title = The Titanic Disaster Hearings\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Gallery Books]]\n| page = 184\n| date = October 2010\n| isbn = 978-1-4516-2347-5}}</ref> Fleet went down to boat deck and helped to prepare [[Lifeboats of the RMS Titanic|Lifeboat No. 6]]. Minutes later, when the boat was already prepared, second officer Lightoller put [[quartermaster]] [[Robert Hichens (sailor)|Robert Hichens]] in charge of the lifeboat and ordered Fleet aboard as well.<ref name=\"herald\"/> As they were lowered away, Hichens and American socialite [[Margaret Brown]] realized there were only two sailors to man the boat, including Fleet and called for another sailor to be sent.<ref name=\"bookbrewster\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Brewster | first1 = Hugh\n| title = Gilded Lives, Fatal Voyage: The Titanic's First-Class Passengers and Their World\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Crown (publisher)|Crown]]\n| pages = \n| date = March 2012\n| isbn = 978-0-307-98481-4}}</ref> As no able seaman was near, Canadian Colonel [[Arthur Godfrey Peuchen]] volunteered to join the boat saying he had experience in sailing. He was ordered by Lightoller to reach the boat by climbing down a rope, which he did successfully.<ref name=\"bookbrewster\"/>\n\nOnce away from the sinking ship, the boat tried to reach the lights of a ship in the distance, thought to be the [[SS Californian|SS ''Californian'']].<ref name=\"walterlord\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Lord | first1 = Walter\n| title = The Complete Titanic Chronicles: A Night to Remember and The Night Lives On\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Open Road Media]]\n| pages = \n| date = March 2013\n| isbn = 978-1-4804-1058-9}}</ref> While Hichens remained at the tiller, Fleet and Peuchen managed the oars. Arguments and problems arose on boat 6 as quartermaster Hichens kept insulting and mistreating the rowers, including Margaret Brown and [[Helen Churchill Candee]]. Later in the night, there was an argument on whether to return for survivors, with Hichens warning against returning saying they would be swamped by swimmers.<ref name=\"bookdummies3\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 51\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> The lifeboat finally reached the [[RMS Carpathia|RMS ''Carpathia'']] by 6:00&nbsp;a.m. on Monday, 15 April 1912.<ref name=\"booktotal\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Shapiro\n| first1 = Marc\n| title = Total Titanic\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Boylston Multimedia]]\n| pages = \n| date = May 2013\n| isbn = 978-0-671-01202-1\n| url = https://archive.org/details/totaltitanicmost00shap\n}}</ref>\n\nAfter the disaster, Fleet underwent two inquiries; first, the [[United States Senate inquiry into the sinking of the RMS Titanic|U.S. Inquiry]] and then the [[British Wreck Commissioner's inquiry into the sinking of the RMS Titanic|British Wreck Commissioner's inquiry]]. In the United States, he was inquired by Senator [[William Alden Smith]], to whom he repeatedly said that had they been equipped with binoculars, the disaster wouldn't have happened.<ref name=\"USInquiry\"/> Before the British Inquiry, he underwent a long examination, often repetitive, for which he refused to answer many of the questions. [[John Bigham, 1st Viscount Mersey|Lord Mersey]], Chairman of the Commission concluded Fleet's interrogation by telling him that he was grateful for his willingness to answer questions despite his wariness when responding to every question. Fleet replied with a sarcastic \"Thanks.\"<ref name=\"bookmark\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Chirnside | first1 = Mark\n| title = The 'Olympic' class ships : Olympic, Titanic, Britannic\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Tempus Publishing|Tempus]]\n| pages = 206, 207\n| year = 2004\n| isbn = 978-0-7524-5895-3}}</ref>\n\n===World Wars and later life===\nFleet served in the ''Titanic''{{'}}s sister ship [[RMS Olympic|RMS ''Olympic'']] before leaving the [[White Star Line]] in August 1912 after noticing that the company treated those involved with the ''Titanic'' differently - in an attempt to forgive what had happened.<ref name=\"bookhooper\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Hooper McCarty\n| first1 = Jennifer\n| last2 = Foecke\n| first2 = Tim\n| title = What Really Sank the Titanic\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Citadel]]; 1 edition\n| page = [https://archive.org/details/whatreallysankti0000mcca/page/230 230]\n| date = February 2008\n| isbn = 978-0-8065-2895-3\n| url = https://archive.org/details/whatreallysankti0000mcca/page/230\n}}</ref> For the next 24 years he sailed for different shipping companies, including the [[Union-Castle Line]]. Fleet served on merchant ships throughout [[World War I]]. Later, he was the ship's lookout again on the [[RMS Olympic|RMS ''Olympic'']], during the 1920s and early 1930s.<ref name=\"seaofglass\">On A Sea Of Glass: The Life & Loss Of The RMS Titanic\" by Tad Fitch, J. Kent Layton & Bill Wormstedt. Amberley Books, March 2012. p 371</ref> When he left the sea in 1936, he was hired by [[Harland & Wolff]] to work at the company's shipyards in [[Southampton]].<ref name=\"bookdummies4\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 47\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> While working there, he lived with his wife's brother. He served again during [[World War II]].<ref name=\"herald\"/>\n\nLater, when he was about to retire, he became a newspaper seller, going through difficult economic times.<ref name=\"bookdummies4\"/>\n\n==Death==\nShortly after Christmas, on 28 December 1964, Fleet's wife died, and her brother evicted him from the house.<ref name=\"maritimequest\">Edmonds, Robert (2009). [http://www.maritimequest.com/liners/titanic/crew/fleet_frederick.htm \"Frederick Fleet(1887\u20131965)\"]. Maritime Quest. Retrieved 12 August 2018.</ref> Consequently, Fleet fell into a downward spiral of [[depression (mood)|depression]] and subsequently [[hanging|hanged]] himself in the house's garden on 10 January 1965.<ref name=\"maritimequest\"/> Fleet was buried in a [[Pauper's funeral|pauper's grave]] at [[Hollybrook Cemetery]], in [[Southampton]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.maritime-executive.com/article/three-men-on-the-titanic |title=Three Men on the Titanic |date=15 April 2018 |access-date=17 July 2019 |magazine=Maritime Executive}}</ref> This grave remained unmarked until 1993, when a headstone bearing an engraving of the ''Titanic'' was erected through donations raised by the [[Titanic Historical Society]].<ref name=\"maritimequest\"/><ref name=\"biography\">[http://www.biography.com/people/frederick-fleet-283644 Frederick Fleet biography] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180323082531/https://www.biography.com/people/frederick-fleet-283644 |date=23 March 2018 }}. [[Biography.com]]. 12 August 2018.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Frederick Fleet}}\n* [http://www.encyclopedia-titanica.org/titanic-survivor/frederick-fleet.html Frederick Fleet Encyclopedia Titanica biography]\n* [http://www.titanicpages.com/frederickfleet Frederick Fleet Titanic Pages biography]\n* {{findagrave|11464660}}\n\n{{RMS Titanic}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fleet, Frederick}}\n[[Category:1887 births]]\n[[Category:1965 deaths]]\n[[Category:British Merchant Navy personnel of World War II]]\n[[Category:British Merchant Service personnel of World War I]]\n[[Category:Burials in Hampshire]]\n[[Category:Sailors from Liverpool]]\n[[Category:RMS Titanic survivors]]\n[[Category:Suicides by hanging in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British sailor}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2012}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Frederick Fleet\n| image = FrederickFleet.April1912.jpg\n| image_size = 250px\n| caption = Fleet in 1912\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|1887|10|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Liverpool]], UK\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|1965|1|10|1887|10|15|df=y}}\n| death_place = [[Southampton]], UK \n| death_cause = [[Suicide by hanging]]\n| birth_name = \n| occupation  = [[Sailor]], [[Crewman]]lookout\n\n| nationality = [[United Kingdom|British]]\n}}\n\n'''Frederick Fleet''' (15 October 1887&nbsp;\u2013 10 January 1965) was a British [[sailor]], [[crewman]] and survivor of the [[Sinking of the RMS Titanic|sinking of the]] {{RMS|Titanic}} after it struck an [[iceberg]] on 14 April 1912.<ref>Fleet was second-in-charge aboard lifeboat #6</ref> Along with fellow lookout [[Reginald Lee]], on duty, aboard the ''Titanic'' when the ship struck the iceberg, contrary to popular belief, Fleet was most likely not the man who spotted the Iceberg. In the enquiry, Fleet stated that the ship began turning immediatly after phoning the bridge about the Iceberg. This leads historians to believe First Officer 'William McMaster Murdoch' was the man to spot the berg. The phone call to the Bridge (answered by 6th Officer Moody) was where Fleet's famous \"Iceberg dead ahead!\" originated.  <ref name=\"USInquiry\">[http://www.titanicinquiry.org/USInq/AmInq04Fleet01.php United States Senate Inquiry Day 4], Testimony of Frederick Fleet.</ref>\n\nFleet testified at the subsequent inquiries into the sinking that, had he and Lee been issued with [[binoculars]]: \"We could have seen it (the iceberg) a bit sooner.\" When asked how much sooner, he responded, \"Well, enough to get out of the way.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.titanicinquiry.org/USInq2/AmInq04Fleet02.php|title=TIP - United States Senate Inquiry - Day 4 - Testimony of Frederick Fleet, cont.|website=www.titanicinquiry.org}}</ref> In later life, Fleet suffered severe [[Major depressive disorder|depression]] and as a result committed suicide by hanging in January 1965.\n\n== Biography ==\n\n=== Early life and sea career ===\nFleet was born in Liverpool on 15 October 1887. He never knew his father, and his mother abandoned him and fled with a boyfriend to [[Springfield, Massachusetts]], in the [[United States]] never to be seen or heard from again.<ref name=\"bookdummies\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 118\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> Frederick was raised by a succession of foster families and distant relatives. In 1903 he went to sea as a deck boy, working his way up to [[able seaman]].<ref name=\"nationalarchivesuk\">[http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/titanic/stories/frederick-fleet.htm Stories from The Titanic], National Archives UK.</ref>\n\nBefore joining the [[Crew of the RMS Titanic|crew of the RMS ''Titanic'']] he had sailed for over four years as a [[lookout]] in the [[RMS Oceanic (1899)|RMS ''Oceanic'']].<ref name=\"nationalarchivesuk\"/> As a seaman, Fleet earned five pounds per month plus an extra 5 [[shilling]]s for lookout duty.<ref name=\"nationalarchivesuk\"/> And it was as a lookout that Fleet joined the ''Titanic'' in April 1912, along with five other watchmen.<ref name=\"nationalarchivesuk\"/>\n\n===R.M.S. ''Titanic''===\n[[Image:Titanic Eisberg.jpg|thumb|right|250px|This iceberg was pictured in the morning of 15 April 1912 and is thought to be the one that the ''Titanic'' had struck.]][[Image:Titanic Bridge and Crow's Nest.png|thumb|left|150px|The crow's nest from which Fleet and Lee spotted the iceberg can be seen in the picture.]]\nFleet boarded the ''Titanic'' in [[Southampton]] on 10 April 1912. The ship made two stops, first in [[Cherbourg, France|Cherbourg]], France and [[Queenstown, Ireland|Queenstown]], in Ireland. The lookouts, six in total, made two-hour shifts due to extreme cold in the crow's nest.<ref name=\"bookseas\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Golden | first1 = Frank\n| last2 = Tipton | first2 = Michael\n| title = Essentials of Sea Survival\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Human Kinetics Pub Inc]]\n| page = 12\n| date = June 2002\n| isbn = 978-0-7360-0215-8}}</ref> The trip was uneventful until the night of 14 April 1912. At 22:00 (10&nbsp;p.m.) that night, Fleet and his fellow lookout [[Reginald Lee]] replaced [[George Symons (RMS Titanic)|George Symons]] and Archie Jewell at the nest.<ref name=\"bookrupert\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Matthews | first1 = Rupert\n| title = Titanic: The Tragic Story of the Ill-fated Ocean Liner\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Arcturus Publishing]]\n| pages = \n| date = March 2011\n| isbn = 1-84837-763-0}}</ref> They passed on the order given earlier to them by second officer [[Charles Lightoller]] to watch out for small ice.<ref name=\"bookdummies1\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 86\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> The night was calm and moonless, which made it difficult to spot the [[iceberg]]s due to the lack of waves breaking against the base of the iceberg and [[Reflection (physics)|reflection]].<ref name=\"Everything Was Against Us\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Angel | first1 = Simon\n| title = The Titanic - \"Everything Was Against Us\"\n| location = \n| publisher = [[CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform]]\n| page = 53\n| date = April 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-4751-2793-5}}</ref> Furthermore, despite Fleet and his fellow lookouts having repeatedly requested being provided with binoculars,<ref>[https://historicsouthampton.wordpress.com/2016/09/18/frederick-fleet/ ''historicsouthampton.wordpress.com/'']</ref><ref>[https://www.encyclopedia-titanica.org/defending-fleet-and-lee.html ''encyclopedia-titanica.org'']</ref> they were not available for the lookouts. It is sometimes attributed to the last-minute change in the hierarchy of the ship when officer [[David Blair (mariner)|David Blair]] was replaced by [[Henry Tingle Wilde]], without Blair mentioning where the binoculars had been located. It has been also mentioned that Blair accidentally took the keys of the cabinet containing the binoculars with him.<ref name=\"blair\">[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-478269/Is-man-sank-Titanic-walking-vital-locker-key.html Is this the man who sank the Titanic by walking off with vital locker key?], [[Daily Mail]].</ref> Despite both inquiries into the disaster, nothing clarified why the lookouts were not provided with binoculars, though there are many explanations such as one that the [[White Star Line]] steamers' lookouts did not particularly use them.<ref name=\"ripples\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Maltin | first1 = Tim\n| last2 = Aston | first2 = Eloise\n| title = 101 Things You Thought You Knew about the Titanic - But Didn't!\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Penguin Books]]\n| page = 33\n| date = November 2011\n| isbn = 978-0-14-311909-8}}</ref> Besides, some experts have said that even using binoculars, neither Fleet nor Lee could have spotted the iceberg any sooner given the conditions of the night.<ref name=\"nbc\">[http://cosmiclog.nbcnews.com/_news/2012/04/01/10970732-10-causes-of-the-titanic-tragedy 10 causes of the Titanic tragedy], NBC news.</ref>\n\nAt 23:39 (11:39&nbsp;p.m.), Fleet first spotted the iceberg and rang the nest's bell three times to warn the bridge of something ahead. Then, using the nest's telephone, he contacted the bridge. It was answered only a few seconds later by sixth officer [[James Paul Moody]], who asked Fleet immediately, \"What did you see?\" He pronounced the infamous \"Iceberg! Right Ahead!\" warning to Moody. Moody acknowledged Fleet's warning, and immediately notified first officer [[William McMaster Murdoch]]; in charge of the bridge.<ref name=\"bookdummies2\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 304\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> After the collision, Fleet and Lee remained on duty for twenty more minutes.<ref name=\"herald\">[http://www.herald-dispatch.com/news/putnam/x1596692627/Fred-Fleet-did-his-duty-on-Titanic-now-resting-in-peace Fred Fleet did his duty on Titanic, now resting in peace], Herald Dispatch.</ref>\n[[Image:Titanicboat6.gif|thumb|right|150px|Lifeboat 6 approaching the [[RMS Carpathia|RMS ''Carpathia'']]; Fleet can be seen trying to tie the boat to the [[davit]]s of the ship.]]\nAt 00:00 (12&nbsp;a.m.), Fleet and Lee were relieved by Alfred Frank Evans and George Hogg.<ref name=\"bookinquiries\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Kuntz | first1 = Tom\n| title = The Titanic Disaster Hearings\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Gallery Books]]\n| page = 184\n| date = October 2010\n| isbn = 978-1-4516-2347-5}}</ref> Fleet went down to boat deck and helped to prepare [[Lifeboats of the RMS Titanic|Lifeboat No. 6]]. Minutes later, when the boat was already prepared, second officer Lightoller put [[quartermaster]] [[Robert Hichens (sailor)|Robert Hichens]] in charge of the lifeboat and ordered Fleet aboard as well.<ref name=\"herald\"/> As they were lowered away, Hichens and American socialite [[Margaret Brown]] realized there were only two sailors to man the boat, including Fleet and called for another sailor to be sent.<ref name=\"bookbrewster\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Brewster | first1 = Hugh\n| title = Gilded Lives, Fatal Voyage: The Titanic's First-Class Passengers and Their World\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Crown (publisher)|Crown]]\n| pages = \n| date = March 2012\n| isbn = 978-0-307-98481-4}}</ref> As no able seaman was near, Canadian Colonel [[Arthur Godfrey Peuchen]] volunteered to join the boat saying he had experience in sailing. He was ordered by Lightoller to reach the boat by climbing down a rope, which he did successfully.<ref name=\"bookbrewster\"/>\n\nOnce away from the sinking ship, the boat tried to reach the lights of a ship in the distance, thought to be the [[SS Californian|SS ''Californian'']].<ref name=\"walterlord\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Lord | first1 = Walter\n| title = The Complete Titanic Chronicles: A Night to Remember and The Night Lives On\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Open Road Media]]\n| pages = \n| date = March 2013\n| isbn = 978-1-4804-1058-9}}</ref> While Hichens remained at the tiller, Fleet and Peuchen managed the oars. Arguments and problems arose on boat 6 as quartermaster Hichens kept insulting and mistreating the rowers, including Margaret Brown and [[Helen Churchill Candee]]. Later in the night, there was an argument on whether to return for survivors, with Hichens warning against returning saying they would be swamped by swimmers.<ref name=\"bookdummies3\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 51\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> The lifeboat finally reached the [[RMS Carpathia|RMS ''Carpathia'']] by 6:00&nbsp;a.m. on Monday, 15 April 1912.<ref name=\"booktotal\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Shapiro\n| first1 = Marc\n| title = Total Titanic\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Boylston Multimedia]]\n| pages = \n| date = May 2013\n| isbn = 978-0-671-01202-1\n| url = https://archive.org/details/totaltitanicmost00shap\n}}</ref>\n\nAfter the disaster, Fleet underwent two inquiries; first, the [[United States Senate inquiry into the sinking of the RMS Titanic|U.S. Inquiry]] and then the [[British Wreck Commissioner's inquiry into the sinking of the RMS Titanic|British Wreck Commissioner's inquiry]]. In the United States, he was inquired by Senator [[William Alden Smith]], to whom he repeatedly said that had they been equipped with binoculars, the disaster wouldn't have happened.<ref name=\"USInquiry\"/> Before the British Inquiry, he underwent a long examination, often repetitive, for which he refused to answer many of the questions. [[John Bigham, 1st Viscount Mersey|Lord Mersey]], Chairman of the Commission concluded Fleet's interrogation by telling him that he was grateful for his willingness to answer questions despite his wariness when responding to every question. Fleet replied with a sarcastic \"Thanks.\"<ref name=\"bookmark\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Chirnside | first1 = Mark\n| title = The 'Olympic' class ships : Olympic, Titanic, Britannic\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Tempus Publishing|Tempus]]\n| pages = 206, 207\n| year = 2004\n| isbn = 978-0-7524-5895-3}}</ref>\n\n===World Wars and later life===\nFleet served in the ''Titanic''{{'}}s sister ship [[RMS Olympic|RMS ''Olympic'']] before leaving the [[White Star Line]] in August 1912 after noticing that the company treated those involved with the ''Titanic'' differently - in an attempt to forgive what had happened.<ref name=\"bookhooper\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Hooper McCarty\n| first1 = Jennifer\n| last2 = Foecke\n| first2 = Tim\n| title = What Really Sank the Titanic\n| location = \n| publisher = [[Citadel]]; 1 edition\n| page = [https://archive.org/details/whatreallysankti0000mcca/page/230 230]\n| date = February 2008\n| isbn = 978-0-8065-2895-3\n| url = https://archive.org/details/whatreallysankti0000mcca/page/230\n}}</ref> For the next 24 years he sailed for different shipping companies, including the [[Union-Castle Line]]. Fleet served on merchant ships throughout [[World War I]]. Later, he was the ship's lookout again on the [[RMS Olympic|RMS ''Olympic'']], during the 1920s and early 1930s.<ref name=\"seaofglass\">On A Sea Of Glass: The Life & Loss Of The RMS Titanic\" by Tad Fitch, J. Kent Layton & Bill Wormstedt. Amberley Books, March 2012. p 371</ref> When he left the sea in 1936, he was hired by [[Harland & Wolff]] to work at the company's shipyards in [[Southampton]].<ref name=\"bookdummies4\">{{cite book\n| last1 = Spignesi | first1 = Stephen J.\n| title = The Titanic For Dummies\n| location = \n| publisher = [[John Wiley & Sons]]\n| page = 47\n| date = January 2012\n| isbn = 978-1-118-17766-2}}</ref> While working there, he lived with his wife's brother. He served again during [[World War II]].<ref name=\"herald\"/>\n\nLater, when he was about to retire, he became a newspaper seller, going through difficult economic times.<ref name=\"bookdummies4\"/>\n\n==Death==\nShortly after Christmas, on 28 December 1964, Fleet's wife died, and her brother evicted him from the house.<ref name=\"maritimequest\">Edmonds, Robert (2009). [http://www.maritimequest.com/liners/titanic/crew/fleet_frederick.htm \"Frederick Fleet(1887\u20131965)\"]. Maritime Quest. Retrieved August 12, 2018.</ref> Consequently, Fleet fell into a downward spiral of [[depression (mood)|depression]] and subsequently [[hanging|hanged]] himself in the house's garden on 10 January 1965.<ref name=\"maritimequest\"/> Fleet was buried in a [[Pauper's funeral|pauper's grave]] at [[Hollybrook Cemetery]], in [[Southampton]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.maritime-executive.com/article/three-men-on-the-titanic |title=Three Men on the Titanic |date=15 April 2018 |access-date=17 July 2019 |magazine=Maritime Executive}}</ref> This grave remained unmarked until 1993, when a headstone bearing an engraving of the ''Titanic'' was erected through donations raised by the [[Titanic Historical Society]].<ref name=\"maritimequest\"/><ref name=\"biography\">[http://www.biography.com/people/frederick-fleet-283644 Frederick Fleet biography] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180323082531/https://www.biography.com/people/frederick-fleet-283644 |date=23 March 2018 }}. [[Biography.com]]. August 12, 2018.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Frederick Fleet}}\n* [http://www.encyclopedia-titanica.org/titanic-survivor/frederick-fleet.html Frederick Fleet Encyclopedia Titanica biography]\n* [http://www.titanicpages.com/frederickfleet Frederick Fleet Titanic Pages biography]\n* {{findagrave|11464660}}\n\n{{RMS Titanic}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fleet, Frederick}}\n[[Category:1887 births]]\n[[Category:1965 deaths]]\n[[Category:British Merchant Navy personnel of World War II]]\n[[Category:British Merchant Service personnel of World War I]]\n[[Category:Burials in Hampshire]]\n[[Category:Sailors from Liverpool]]\n[[Category:RMS Titanic survivors]]\n[[Category:Suicides by hanging in England]]\n", "name_user": "John B123", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederick_Fleet"}
{"title_page": "Lake Eyre", "text_new": "{{other uses|Lake Eyre (disambiguation){{!}}Lake Eyre}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=May 2011}}\n{{Infobox lake\n |name = Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre\n |image = NEO lake eyre big.jpg\n |image_size = 280\n |caption = Composite [[Landsat 7]] satellite image in 1999 using shortwave infrared, near-infrared, and blue wavelengths\n |image_bathymetry = Lake eyre basin map.png\n |bathymetry_size = 280\n |caption_bathymetry = A map of the [[Lake Eyre basin]], with the lake at bottom left\n |location = [[Far North (South Australia)|Northern]] [[South Australia]]\n |coords = {{coord|28|22||S|137|22||E|region:AU-SA_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}}\n |lake_type = [[Ancient lake]], [[Endorheic]]\n |inflow = [[Warburton River]]\n |outflow = ''[[Evaporation]]''\n |catchment = \n |basin_countries = Australia\n |length = \n |width = \n |area = {{convert|9500|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}} (max)\n |depth = {{convert|1.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} (every 3 years), {{convert|4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} (every decade)\n |max-depth =\n |volume = \n |residence_time = \n |shore = \n |elevation = {{convert|-9|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} {{small|(shoreline when full)}};<br />{{convert|-15|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} {{small|(lowest point when empty)}}\n |islands = \n |cities = \n}}\n'''Lake Eyre''' ({{IPAc-en|\u025b\u0259r}} {{respell|AIR}}), [[Dual naming|officially known]] as '''Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre''',<ref name=Tradname>{{cite web |last=|first=|title=New name adopted for outback Lake Eyre|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|date=19 December 2012|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-12-19/new-name-adopted-for-outback-lake-eyre/4436212\n|accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> contains the lowest natural point in Australia, at approximately {{convert|12|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[below sea level]] ([[Australian Height Datum|AHD]]), and, on the rare occasions that it fills, is the largest lake in Australia, covering {{convert|9500|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}}. The shallow [[endorheic]] lake is the [[depocentre]] of the vast [[Lake Eyre basin]] and is found in [[Far North (South Australia)|Northern]] [[South Australia]], some {{convert|700|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} north of [[Adelaide]].\n\nWhen the lake is full, it has the same [[salinity]] level as the sea, but as the lake dries up and the water evaporates, salinity increases.\n\nThe lake was named by Europeans in honour of [[Edward John Eyre]], who was the first European to see it, in 1840. The lake's official name was changed in December 2012 to combine the name \"Lake Eyre\" with the indigenous name, '''Kati Thanda'''.<ref name=\"Tradname\"/> The [[Native title in Australia|native title]] over the lake and surrounding region is held by the [[Arabana language|Arabana people]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-05-22/native-title-arbana-hearing/4025738 |title=Federal Court awards native title over Lake Eyre |work=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |location=Australia |date=23 May 2012 |accessdate=2 January 2012 }}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:LakeEyreSaltCrust.JPG|thumb|left|Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre salt crust]]\n[[File:Lake eyre.JPG|thumb|Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre seen from an aircraft, showing pink colouration from algae]]\n[[File:Lake Eyre.JPG|thumb|Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre South]]\nKati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre is in the [[Deserts of Australia|deserts]] of [[central Australia]], in northern South Australia. The Lake Eyre Basin is a large [[Endorheic basin|endorheic]] system surrounding the lakebed, the lowest part of which is filled with the characteristic [[salt pan (geology)|salt pan]] caused by the seasonal expansion and subsequent [[evaporation]] of the trapped waters. Even in the [[dry season]], there is usually some water remaining in Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre, normally collecting in over 200 smaller sub-lakes within its margins. The lake was formed by [[aeolian processes]] after tectonic [[Anticline|upwarping]] occurred to the south subsequent to the end of the [[Pleistocene]] epoch.<ref name=\"lhlrr\"/>\n\nDuring the [[Wet season|rainy season]], rivers from the north-east part of the Lake Eyre Basin\u2014in [[outback]] (south-west and central) Queensland\u2014flow towards the lake through the [[Channel Country]]. The amount of water from the [[monsoon]] determines whether water will reach the lake and, if it does, how deep the lake will get. The average rainfall in the area of the lake is {{convert|100|to|150|mm}} per year.<ref name=\"lhlrr\">{{cite book |title=The Lakes Handbook: Lake Restoration and Rehabilitation, Volume 2 |last=O'Sullivan |first=Patrick |author2=C. S. Reynolds  |year=2008 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=1405141107 |pages=233\u2013235 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bibY60NWOlEC |accessdate=23 December 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe {{convert|-15|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} altitude usually attributed to Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre refers to the deepest parts of the lake floor, in Belt Bay and the Madigan Gulf. The shoreline lies at {{convert|-9|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>[http://www.ilec.or.jp/database/oce/oce-04.html Lake Eyre] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120523201740/http://www.ilec.or.jp/database/oce/oce-04.html |date=23 May 2012 }}. International Lake Environment Committee. Retrieved 29 March 2012.</ref> The lake is the area of maximum deposition of sediment in the Lake Eyre Basin.<ref name=\"dde\">{{cite book|title=Deserts and Desert Environments |last=Laity |first=Julie J. |year=2009 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=1444300741 |pages=112 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wtAbzLLTcwcC |accessdate=20 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nLake Eyre is divided into two sections which are joined by the Goyder Channel. These are known as Lake Eyre North, which is {{convert|144|km}} in length and {{convert|65|km}} wide, and Lake Eyre South, which measures {{convert|65|by|24|km}}.<ref name=\"law\">{{cite book |title=Lakes and Wetland |last=Rafferty |first=John P. |year=2007 |publisher=The Rosen Publishing Group |isbn=1615303200 |page=186 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=StCGBdKR4qgC |accessdate=20 December 2012 }}</ref> The salt crusts are thickest\u2014up to {{convert|50|cm|abbr=on}}\u2014in the southern Belt Bay, Jackboot Bay and Madigan Gulf sub-basins of Lake Eyre North.<ref>Dulhunty, J.A. (1990): Lake Eyre, In: M.J. Tyler, [[Charles Rowland Twidale|C.R. Twidale]], M. Davis and C.B. Walker, ''Natural History of the North East Deserts.'' Royal Society of South Australia Inc. Pp. 101-4. {{ISBN|0-9596627-5-8}}</ref>\n\nSince 1883, proposals have been made to flood Lake Eyre with seawater brought to the basin via a canal or pipeline. The purpose was, in part, to increase evaporation and thereby increase rainfall in the region downwind of an enlarged Lake Eyre.<ref>Badescu, V., Cathcart, R.B., Bolonkin, A.A., Paulescu, M. and Gravila, P. (2013) Macro-engineering Australia's Lake Eyre with imported seawater. ''International Journal of Environment and Sustainable Development'' 12: 264-284.</ref> The added rainfall has been modeled as small.<ref>Hope, Pandora & Nicholls, Neville & L. McGregor, John. (2004). \"[https://www.researchgate.net/publication/239585647_The_rainfall_response_to_permanent_inland_water_in_Australia The rainfall response to permanent inland water in Australia]\" Aust. Meteorol. Mag.</ref> Due to the basin's low elevation below sea level and the region's high annual evaporation rate (between {{convert|2500|and|3500|mm}}<ref>Badman, F.J. (1991): Introduction. In: F.J. Badman, B.K. Arnold and S.L. Belt, ''A Natural History of the Lake Eyre Region.'' The South Australian National Parks and Wildlife Service's Northern Consultative Committee. P 1. {{ISBN|0 646 07183 1}}</ref>), such schemes have generally been considered impractical, as it is likely that accumulation of salt deposits would rapidly block the engineered channel.<ref>[http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article27516822 The Plan To Fill Lake Eyre] TROVE: ''The Sydney Morning Herald'', 27 May 1954. Retrieved 8 February 2016.</ref> At a rate of {{convert|1|cm|abbr=on}} evaporation per day, a {{convert|3|m|abbr=on}} viaduct flowing a {{convert|0.5|m/s|abbr=on}} would supply enough water to create a {{convert|100|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} sea. If brine water was not sent back to the ocean, it would precipitate {{convert|90000|LT}} of salt every year.{{Citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\n==Salinity==\nThe [[Salinity in Australia|salinity]] in the lake increases as the {{convert|450|mm|in|0|abbr=on}} salt crust dissolves over a period of six months of a major flood, resulting in a massive [[fish kill]]. When over {{convert|4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} deep, the lake is no more salty than the [[World Ocean|sea]], but salinity increases as the water evaporates, with [[Saturated solution|saturation]] occurring at about a {{convert|500|mm|in|0|abbr=on}} depth. The lake takes on a pink hue when saturated, due to the presence of [[beta-carotene]] pigment caused by the [[alga]] ''[[Dunaliella salina]]''.\n\n== History ==\n''[[Wangkangurru]] (''also known as ''Arabana/Wangkangurru, Wangganguru, Wanggangurru, Wongkangurru)'' is an [[Australian Aboriginal languages|Australian Aboriginal language]] spoken on Wangkangurru country. It is closely related to [[Arabana language]] of [[South Australia]]. The Wangkangurru language region was traditionally in the South Australian-Queensland border region taking in [[Birdsville]] and extending south towards [[Innamincka, South Australia|Innamincka]] and Lake Eyre, including the local government areas of the [[Shire of Diamantina]] as well as the [[Outback Communities Authority]] of South Australia''.<ref>{{Cite SLQ-CC-BY|url=https://maps.slq.qld.gov.au/iyil/view/178|title=Wangkangurru|author=|date=|website=Queensland Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander languages map|access-date=23 January 2020}}</ref>''\n\n==Floods==\nTypically a {{convert|1.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} flood occurs every three years, a {{convert|4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} flood every decade, and a fill or near fill a few times a century. The water in the lake soon evaporates, with a minor or medium flood drying by the end of the following summer. Most of the water entering the lakes arrives via [[Warburton River]].<ref name=\"lhlrr\"/>\n\nIn strong [[La Ni\u00f1a]] years, the lake can fill. Since 1885, this has occurred in 1886\u20131887, 1889\u20131890, 1916\u20131917, [[1950 Australian rainfall records|1950]], 1955, 1974\u20131977,<ref>Allen, Robert J.; The ''Australasian Summer Monsoon, Teleconnections, and Flooding in the Lake Eyre Basin''; published 1985 by Royal Geographical Society of Australasia, S.A. Branch; {{ISBN|0-909112-09-6}}</ref> and 1999\u20132001,<ref>[[Australian Bureau of Meteorology]]; ''Annual Climate Summary'' (2000)</ref> with the highest flood of {{convert|6|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} in 1974. Local rain can also fill Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre to {{convert|3|\u2013|4|m|ft|abbr=on}}, as occurred in 1984 and 1989. Torrential rain in January 2007 took about six weeks to reach the lake but only placed a small amount of water into it.<ref name =\"ABC8March2007\">{{cite news|url= http://www.abc.net.au/news/newsitems/200703/s1866774.htm|title=Lake Eyre flooding attracts yachting club interest|work=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |location=Australia |date=8 March 2007|accessdate=8 March 2007}}</ref>\n\nWhen recently flooded, the lake is almost fresh, and native freshwater fish, including [[bony bream]] (''Nematolosa erebi''), the Lake Eyre Basin sub-species of [[golden perch]] (''Macquaria ambigua'') and various small [[Craterocephalus|hardyhead]] species (''Craterocephalus'' spp.) can survive in it. \n\n===2009 to 2011===\n[[File:STS035-502-4.jpg|thumb|right|Lake Eyre in 1990, as seen from the  [[Space Shuttle Columbia|Space Shuttle ''Columbia'']]]]\nThe 2009 Lake Eyre flood peaked at {{convert|1.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} deep in late May, which is a quarter of its maximum recorded depth of {{convert|6|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}. {{convert|9|km3|cumi|0|abbr=on}} of water crossed the Queensland\u2013South Australian border with most of it coming from massive floods in the [[Georgina River]]. However, owing to the very low rainfall in the lower reaches of these rivers (contrasting with heavy rainfall in the upper catchments),<ref>[http://www.bom.gov.au/climate/annual_sum/2009/AnClimSum09_HR1.1.pdf Australian Annual Climate Summary 2009]</ref> the greater proportion soaked into the desert or evaporated en route to the lake, leaving less than {{convert|4|km3|cumi|abbr=on}} in the lake, which covered an area of {{convert|800|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}}, or 12% of the total. As the flood did not start filling the lake's deepest point (Belt Bay) until late March, little bird life appeared, preferring instead to nest in the upper reaches of the Lake Eyre Basin, north of [[Birdsville]], where large lakes appeared in January as a result of monsoonal rain.{{cn|date=May 2019}}\n\nThe high rainfall in summer 2010 sent flood water into the [[Diamantina River|Diamantina]], [[Georgina River|Georgina]] and [[Cooper Creek]] catchments of the Lake Eyre basin, with the Cooper Creek reaching the lake for the first time since 1990. The higher rainfall prompted many different birds to migrate back to the area for breeding.<ref>[http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/journal/lake-eyre-floods-again.htm/ Lake Eyre floods again] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130515222926/http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/journal/lake-eyre-floods-again.htm/ |date=15 May 2013 }}, Australian Geographic, 15 July 2010</ref>\n\nHeavy local rain in early March 2011 in the Stuart Creek and Warriner catchments filled Lake Eyre South, with Lake Eyre North about 75 per cent covered with water firstly from the [[Neales River|Neales]] and [[Macumba River|Macumba]] Rivers, and later from the [[Warburton River]].<ref>{{cite news |date=9 March 2011 |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2011/03/09/3159183.htm?section=justin/ |title=Flooding and storms fill outback lake |work=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |location=Australia |accessdate=29 March 2012 }}</ref>\n\n=== 2015 to 2016 ===\nIn late 2015, water began flowing into Lake Eyre following heavy rain in the north-east of the state.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Lake Eyre begins filling with water after soaking rains|url = http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-01-02/lake-eyre-begins-filling-with-water-after-soaking-rains/7064248|website = ABC News|accessdate = 2016-01-04|language = en-AU}}</ref>\n\n===2019===\n\nIn late March 2019, floodwaters began arriving as a result of torrential rains in [[northern Queensland]] in January. In the past, the water had taken anywhere from three to 10 months to reach the lake, but this time it arrived in two. The first flooding would be closely followed by another surge, following rains produced by [[2018\u201319_Australian_region_cyclone_season#Severe_Tropical_Cyclone_Trevor|Cyclone Trevor]]. Traditional owners and graziers agree that it is essential that the river run its course and should not be harvested during floods, as any interference in the natural systems could damage the [[ecosystem]].<ref name=ABCflood>{{cite news|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation News|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-05-09/lake-eyre-is-a-wild-river-system-left-to-run-its-course/11035506|title=Wild Abandon|series=7:30|first= Dominique|last= Schwartz|others=Photography by Brendan Esposito|date= 9 May 2019|accessdate=9 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Yacht club==\nThe Lake Eyre Yacht Club is a dedicated group of sailors who sail on the lake's floods, including recent trips in 1997, 2000, 2001, 2004, 2007 and 2009.<ref>[http://www.lakeeyreyc.com Welcome to the Lake Eyre Yacht Club]. Retrieved 29 March 2012.</ref> A number of {{convert|6|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[trailer sailer]]s sailed on Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre in 1975, 1976, and 1984, when the flood depth reached {{convert|3|\u2013|6|m|ft|abbr=on}}. In July 2010 The Yacht Club held its first regatta since 1976<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.lakepedia.com/lake/eyre.html |title=Lake Eyre - 9,690 km2 - Facts, Map, Activities|work=www.lakepedia.com |accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref> and its first on Lake Killamperpunna, a freshwater lake on Cooper Creek. The Cooper had reached Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre for the first time since 1990.{{Citation needed|date=April 2016}}\n\nWhen the lake is full, a notable phenomenon is that around midday the surface can often become very flat. The surface then reflects the sky in a way that leaves both the horizon and water surface virtually impossible to see. The commodore of the Lake Eyre Yacht Club has stated that sailing during this time has the appearance of sailing in the sky.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tinson|first1=Sam|title=Dry country|url=http://www.sailsmagazine.com.au/j/index.php/livenews/101-dry-country|accessdate=30 March 2017|work=Sails Magazine|issue=7|date=May 2011|language=en-gb|quote=\u201cOften you get becalmed in the middle of the lake at midday, and the surface is like a mirror, the water and the sky become one. You get a light sea fog and it\u2019s almost like you\u2019re floating in a cloud. It\u2019s a very beautiful thing.\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170331120051/http://www.sailsmagazine.com.au/j/index.php/livenews/101-dry-country|archive-date=31 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Land speed record attempts==\n[[File:EyreCampbellPlaque.JPG|thumb|Campbell plaque at Level Post Bay]]\n\nKati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre has been a site for various [[land speed record]] attempts on its [[Salt pan (geology)|salt flats]], similar to those found in the [[Bonneville Salt Flats]], especially those by [[Donald Campbell]] with the [[Bluebird-Proteus CN7]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Bluebird and the Dead Lake |author=[[John Pearson (author)]] |url= https://books.google.com/books/about/Bluebird_and_the_Dead_Lake.html?id=VuEBAAAACAAJ&redir_esc=y }}</ref>\n\n==Wildlife==\nPhytoplankton in the lake includes ''[[Nodularia|Nodularia spumigena]]'' and a number of species of ''[[Dunaliella]]''.<ref name=\"lhlrr\"/>\n\n===Birds===\nBirds such as [[Australian pelican|pelicans]] and [[banded stilt]]s are drawn to a filled lake from southern coastal regions of Australia, and from as far afield as Papua New Guinea. During the 1989\u20131990 flood, it was estimated that 200,000 pelicans, 80% of Australia's total population, came to feed & roost at Lake Eyre.<ref name=\"wdrwsg\">{{cite book |title=Why Does the World Stay Green?: Nutrition and Survival of Plant-eaters |last=TCR |first=White |year=2005 |publisher=Csiro Publishing |isbn=0643099816 |page=88 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Zf6pZp20qxEC |accessdate=20 December 2012 }}</ref> Scientists are presently unable to determine how such birds appear able to detect the filling of the lake, even when hundreds or thousands of kilometres away from the basin.<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-01-06/birds-set-to-return-to-lake-eyre-to-breed/7069228?section=sa Birds set to return to Lake Eyre to breed as inland lakes fill with water] ''ABC News'', 6 January 2016. Accessed 6 January 2016.</ref>\n\n==Protected area status==\n\n===Statutory===\nThe extent of the lake is covered by two [[protected area]]s declared by the [[Government of South Australia]] - the [[Kati Thanda-Lake Eyre National Park]] and the [[Elliot Price Conservation Park]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kati Thanda-Lake Eyre National Park Map|url=http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/files/0bf2b3b7-6c15-4f45-a704-a3dc00c3a14a/kati-thanda-lake-eyre-national-park-map.pdf|publisher=Department of Environment, Water and Natural Resources|accessdate=5 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Non-statutory===\n\n====Wetlands====\nLake Eyre is on the list of wetlands of national importance known as [[A Directory of Important Wetlands in Australia]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Eyles|first1=Kathy|title=A Directory of important wetlands in Australia|date=2001|publisher=Environment Australia|isbn=978-0-642-54721-7|page=78|edition=3|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/system/files/resources/18f0bb21-b67c-4e99-a155-cb5255398568/files/directory-ch9.pdf|accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Important bird area====\nLake Eyre has been identified by [[BirdLife International]] as an [[Important Bird Area]] (IBA) known as the Lake Eyre Important Bird Area, because, when flooded, it supports major breeding events of the [[Banded stilt]] and [[Australian pelican]], as well as over 1% of the world populations of [[Red-necked avocet]]s, [[Sharp-tailed sandpiper]]s, [[Red-necked stint]]s, [[Silver gull]]s and [[Caspian tern]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.birdlife.org/datazone/sitefactsheet.php?id=24442 |title= Important Bird Areas factsheet: Lake Eyre |accessdate=5 February 2015 |work= Birdata |publisher=Birdlife International }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{stack|{{portal|Australia}}}}\n* [[Lake Torrens]]\n* [[List of lakes of Australia]]\n* [[Pluvial lake]]\n*[[Eyre (disambiguation)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Commons category|Lake Eyre}}\n\n* {{cite web|format=video|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-05-09/the-re-birth-of-lake-eyre/11099272|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|website=ABC News|series=7:30 Report|title=The re-birth of Lake Eyre|first=Dominique|last=Schwarz|date=10 May 2019}}\n\n*Dr Vincent Kotwicki: ''[http://www.k26.com/eyre/ Floods of Lake Eyre]''  - interesting site with lots of data, including Lake Eyre inflows 1885-2012.\n*[http://www.saltdoco.com/movie-info/synopsis.htm ''Salt''] - documentary film by Murray Fredericks and Michael Angus (synopsis)\n\n*[[NASA Earth Observatory]]: [http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=38994 Lake Eyre Filling Peaks - 21 June 2009]\n\n*[http://www.LakeEyreYC.com Lake Eyre Yacht Club website]\n{{Oceania topic|List of lakes of|title=List of lakes in Oceania}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lake Eyre}}\n[[Category:Ancient lakes]]\n[[Category:Saline lakes of South Australia|Eyre, Lake]]\n[[Category:Endorheic lakes of Australia|Eyre, Lake]]\n[[Category:Lake Eyre basin]]\n[[Category:Far North (South Australia)]]\n[[Category:Extreme points of Australia]]\n[[Category:Lowest points]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses|Lake Eyre (disambiguation){{!}}Lake Eyre}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=May 2011}}\n{{Infobox lake\n |name = Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre\n |image = NEO lake eyre big.jpg\n |image_size = 280\n |caption = Composite [[Landsat 7]] satellite image in 1999 using shortwave infrared, near-infrared, and blue wavelengths\n |image_bathymetry = Lake eyre basin map.png\n |bathymetry_size = 280\n |caption_bathymetry = A map of the [[Lake Eyre basin]], with the lake at bottom left\n |location = [[Far North (South Australia)|Northern]] [[South Australia]]\n |coords = {{coord|28|22||S|137|22||E|region:AU-SA_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}}\n |lake_type = [[Ancient lake]], [[Endorheic]]\n |inflow = [[Warburton River]]\n |outflow = ''[[Evaporation]]''\n |catchment = \n |basin_countries = Australia\n |length = \n |width = \n |area = {{convert|9500|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}} (max)\n |depth = {{convert|1.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} (every 3 years), {{convert|4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} (every decade)\n |max-depth =\n |volume = \n |residence_time = \n |shore = \n |elevation = {{convert|-9|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} {{small|(shoreline when full)}};<br />{{convert|-15|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} {{small|(lowest point when empty)}}\n |islands = \n |cities = \n}}\n'''Lake Eyre''' ({{IPAc-en|\u025b\u0259r}} {{respell|AIR}}), [[Dual naming|officially known]] as '''Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre''',<ref name=Tradname>{{cite web |last=|first=|title=New name adopted for outback Lake Eyre|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|date=19 December 2012|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-12-19/new-name-adopted-for-outback-lake-eyre/4436212\n|accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> contains the lowest natural point in Australia, at approximately {{convert|15|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[below sea level]] ([[Australian Height Datum|AHD]]), and, on the rare occasions that it fills, is the largest lake in Australia, covering {{convert|9500|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}}. The shallow [[endorheic]] lake is the [[depocentre]] of the vast [[Lake Eyre basin]] and is found in [[Far North (South Australia)|Northern]] [[South Australia]], some {{convert|700|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} north of [[Adelaide]].\n\nWhen the lake is full, it has the same [[salinity]] level as the sea, but as the lake dries up and the water evaporates, salinity increases.\n\nThe lake was named by Europeans in honour of [[Edward John Eyre]], who was the first European to see it, in 1840. The lake's official name was changed in December 2012 to combine the name \"Lake Eyre\" with the indigenous name, '''Kati Thanda'''.<ref name=\"Tradname\"/> The [[Native title in Australia|native title]] over the lake and surrounding region is held by the [[Arabana language|Arabana people]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2012-05-22/native-title-arbana-hearing/4025738 |title=Federal Court awards native title over Lake Eyre |work=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |location=Australia |date=23 May 2012 |accessdate=2 January 2012 }}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:LakeEyreSaltCrust.JPG|thumb|left|Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre salt crust]]\n[[File:Lake eyre.JPG|thumb|Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre seen from an aircraft, showing pink colouration from algae]]\n[[File:Lake Eyre.JPG|thumb|Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre South]]\nKati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre is in the [[Deserts of Australia|deserts]] of [[central Australia]], in northern South Australia. The Lake Eyre Basin is a large [[Endorheic basin|endorheic]] system surrounding the lakebed, the lowest part of which is filled with the characteristic [[salt pan (geology)|salt pan]] caused by the seasonal expansion and subsequent [[evaporation]] of the trapped waters. Even in the [[dry season]], there is usually some water remaining in Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre, normally collecting in over 200 smaller sub-lakes within its margins. The lake was formed by [[aeolian processes]] after tectonic [[Anticline|upwarping]] occurred to the south subsequent to the end of the [[Pleistocene]] epoch.<ref name=\"lhlrr\"/>\n\nDuring the [[Wet season|rainy season]], rivers from the north-east part of the Lake Eyre Basin\u2014in [[outback]] (south-west and central) Queensland\u2014flow towards the lake through the [[Channel Country]]. The amount of water from the [[monsoon]] determines whether water will reach the lake and, if it does, how deep the lake will get. The average rainfall in the area of the lake is {{convert|100|to|150|mm}} per year.<ref name=\"lhlrr\">{{cite book |title=The Lakes Handbook: Lake Restoration and Rehabilitation, Volume 2 |last=O'Sullivan |first=Patrick |author2=C. S. Reynolds  |year=2008 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=1405141107 |pages=233\u2013235 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bibY60NWOlEC |accessdate=23 December 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe {{convert|-15|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} altitude usually attributed to Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre refers to the deepest parts of the lake floor, in Belt Bay and the Madigan Gulf. The shoreline lies at {{convert|-9|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>[http://www.ilec.or.jp/database/oce/oce-04.html Lake Eyre] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120523201740/http://www.ilec.or.jp/database/oce/oce-04.html |date=23 May 2012 }}. International Lake Environment Committee. Retrieved 29 March 2012.</ref> The lake is the area of maximum deposition of sediment in the Lake Eyre Basin.<ref name=\"dde\">{{cite book|title=Deserts and Desert Environments |last=Laity |first=Julie J. |year=2009 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=1444300741 |pages=112 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wtAbzLLTcwcC |accessdate=20 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nLake Eyre is divided into two sections which are joined by the Goyder Channel. These are known as Lake Eyre North, which is {{convert|144|km}} in length and {{convert|65|km}} wide, and Lake Eyre South, which measures {{convert|65|by|24|km}}.<ref name=\"law\">{{cite book |title=Lakes and Wetland |last=Rafferty |first=John P. |year=2007 |publisher=The Rosen Publishing Group |isbn=1615303200 |page=186 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=StCGBdKR4qgC |accessdate=20 December 2012 }}</ref> The salt crusts are thickest\u2014up to {{convert|50|cm|abbr=on}}\u2014in the southern Belt Bay, Jackboot Bay and Madigan Gulf sub-basins of Lake Eyre North.<ref>Dulhunty, J.A. (1990): Lake Eyre, In: M.J. Tyler, [[Charles Rowland Twidale|C.R. Twidale]], M. Davis and C.B. Walker, ''Natural History of the North East Deserts.'' Royal Society of South Australia Inc. Pp. 101-4. {{ISBN|0-9596627-5-8}}</ref>\n\nSince 1883, proposals have been made to flood Lake Eyre with seawater brought to the basin via a canal or pipeline. The purpose was, in part, to increase evaporation and thereby increase rainfall in the region downwind of an enlarged Lake Eyre.<ref>Badescu, V., Cathcart, R.B., Bolonkin, A.A., Paulescu, M. and Gravila, P. (2013) Macro-engineering Australia's Lake Eyre with imported seawater. ''International Journal of Environment and Sustainable Development'' 12: 264-284.</ref> The added rainfall has been modeled as small.<ref>Hope, Pandora & Nicholls, Neville & L. McGregor, John. (2004). \"[https://www.researchgate.net/publication/239585647_The_rainfall_response_to_permanent_inland_water_in_Australia The rainfall response to permanent inland water in Australia]\" Aust. Meteorol. Mag.</ref> Due to the basin's low elevation below sea level and the region's high annual evaporation rate (between {{convert|2500|and|3500|mm}}<ref>Badman, F.J. (1991): Introduction. In: F.J. Badman, B.K. Arnold and S.L. Belt, ''A Natural History of the Lake Eyre Region.'' The South Australian National Parks and Wildlife Service's Northern Consultative Committee. P 1. {{ISBN|0 646 07183 1}}</ref>), such schemes have generally been considered impractical, as it is likely that accumulation of salt deposits would rapidly block the engineered channel.<ref>[http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article27516822 The Plan To Fill Lake Eyre] TROVE: ''The Sydney Morning Herald'', 27 May 1954. Retrieved 8 February 2016.</ref> At a rate of {{convert|1|cm|abbr=on}} evaporation per day, a {{convert|3|m|abbr=on}} viaduct flowing a {{convert|0.5|m/s|abbr=on}} would supply enough water to create a {{convert|100|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} sea. If brine water was not sent back to the ocean, it would precipitate {{convert|90000|LT}} of salt every year.{{Citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\n==Salinity==\nThe [[Salinity in Australia|salinity]] in the lake increases as the {{convert|450|mm|in|0|abbr=on}} salt crust dissolves over a period of six months of a major flood, resulting in a massive [[fish kill]]. When over {{convert|4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} deep, the lake is no more salty than the [[World Ocean|sea]], but salinity increases as the water evaporates, with [[Saturated solution|saturation]] occurring at about a {{convert|500|mm|in|0|abbr=on}} depth. The lake takes on a pink hue when saturated, due to the presence of [[beta-carotene]] pigment caused by the [[alga]] ''[[Dunaliella salina]]''.\n\n== History ==\n''[[Wangkangurru]] (''also known as ''Arabana/Wangkangurru, Wangganguru, Wanggangurru, Wongkangurru)'' is an [[Australian Aboriginal languages|Australian Aboriginal language]] spoken on Wangkangurru country. It is closely related to [[Arabana language]] of [[South Australia]]. The Wangkangurru language region was traditionally in the South Australian-Queensland border region taking in [[Birdsville]] and extending south towards [[Innamincka, South Australia|Innamincka]] and Lake Eyre, including the local government areas of the [[Shire of Diamantina]] as well as the [[Outback Communities Authority]] of South Australia''.<ref>{{Cite SLQ-CC-BY|url=https://maps.slq.qld.gov.au/iyil/view/178|title=Wangkangurru|author=|date=|website=Queensland Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander languages map|access-date=23 January 2020}}</ref>''\n\n==Floods==\nTypically a {{convert|1.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} flood occurs every three years, a {{convert|4|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} flood every decade, and a fill or near fill a few times a century. The water in the lake soon evaporates, with a minor or medium flood drying by the end of the following summer. Most of the water entering the lakes arrives via [[Warburton River]].<ref name=\"lhlrr\"/>\n\nIn strong [[La Ni\u00f1a]] years, the lake can fill. Since 1885, this has occurred in 1886\u20131887, 1889\u20131890, 1916\u20131917, [[1950 Australian rainfall records|1950]], 1955, 1974\u20131977,<ref>Allen, Robert J.; The ''Australasian Summer Monsoon, Teleconnections, and Flooding in the Lake Eyre Basin''; published 1985 by Royal Geographical Society of Australasia, S.A. Branch; {{ISBN|0-909112-09-6}}</ref> and 1999\u20132001,<ref>[[Australian Bureau of Meteorology]]; ''Annual Climate Summary'' (2000)</ref> with the highest flood of {{convert|6|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} in 1974. Local rain can also fill Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre to {{convert|3|\u2013|4|m|ft|abbr=on}}, as occurred in 1984 and 1989. Torrential rain in January 2007 took about six weeks to reach the lake but only placed a small amount of water into it.<ref name =\"ABC8March2007\">{{cite news|url= http://www.abc.net.au/news/newsitems/200703/s1866774.htm|title=Lake Eyre flooding attracts yachting club interest|work=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |location=Australia |date=8 March 2007|accessdate=8 March 2007}}</ref>\n\nWhen recently flooded, the lake is almost fresh, and native freshwater fish, including [[bony bream]] (''Nematolosa erebi''), the Lake Eyre Basin sub-species of [[golden perch]] (''Macquaria ambigua'') and various small [[Craterocephalus|hardyhead]] species (''Craterocephalus'' spp.) can survive in it. \n\n===2009 to 2011===\n[[File:STS035-502-4.jpg|thumb|right|Lake Eyre in 1990, as seen from the  [[Space Shuttle Columbia|Space Shuttle ''Columbia'']]]]\nThe 2009 Lake Eyre flood peaked at {{convert|1.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} deep in late May, which is a quarter of its maximum recorded depth of {{convert|6|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}. {{convert|9|km3|cumi|0|abbr=on}} of water crossed the Queensland\u2013South Australian border with most of it coming from massive floods in the [[Georgina River]]. However, owing to the very low rainfall in the lower reaches of these rivers (contrasting with heavy rainfall in the upper catchments),<ref>[http://www.bom.gov.au/climate/annual_sum/2009/AnClimSum09_HR1.1.pdf Australian Annual Climate Summary 2009]</ref> the greater proportion soaked into the desert or evaporated en route to the lake, leaving less than {{convert|4|km3|cumi|abbr=on}} in the lake, which covered an area of {{convert|800|km2|sqmi|0|abbr=on}}, or 12% of the total. As the flood did not start filling the lake's deepest point (Belt Bay) until late March, little bird life appeared, preferring instead to nest in the upper reaches of the Lake Eyre Basin, north of [[Birdsville]], where large lakes appeared in January as a result of monsoonal rain.{{cn|date=May 2019}}\n\nThe high rainfall in summer 2010 sent flood water into the [[Diamantina River|Diamantina]], [[Georgina River|Georgina]] and [[Cooper Creek]] catchments of the Lake Eyre basin, with the Cooper Creek reaching the lake for the first time since 1990. The higher rainfall prompted many different birds to migrate back to the area for breeding.<ref>[http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/journal/lake-eyre-floods-again.htm/ Lake Eyre floods again] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130515222926/http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/journal/lake-eyre-floods-again.htm/ |date=15 May 2013 }}, Australian Geographic, 15 July 2010</ref>\n\nHeavy local rain in early March 2011 in the Stuart Creek and Warriner catchments filled Lake Eyre South, with Lake Eyre North about 75 per cent covered with water firstly from the [[Neales River|Neales]] and [[Macumba River|Macumba]] Rivers, and later from the [[Warburton River]].<ref>{{cite news |date=9 March 2011 |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2011/03/09/3159183.htm?section=justin/ |title=Flooding and storms fill outback lake |work=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |location=Australia |accessdate=29 March 2012 }}</ref>\n\n=== 2015 to 2016 ===\nIn late 2015, water began flowing into Lake Eyre following heavy rain in the north-east of the state.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Lake Eyre begins filling with water after soaking rains|url = http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-01-02/lake-eyre-begins-filling-with-water-after-soaking-rains/7064248|website = ABC News|accessdate = 2016-01-04|language = en-AU}}</ref>\n\n===2019===\n\nIn late March 2019, floodwaters began arriving as a result of torrential rains in [[northern Queensland]] in January. In the past, the water had taken anywhere from three to 10 months to reach the lake, but this time it arrived in two. The first flooding would be closely followed by another surge, following rains produced by [[2018\u201319_Australian_region_cyclone_season#Severe_Tropical_Cyclone_Trevor|Cyclone Trevor]]. Traditional owners and graziers agree that it is essential that the river run its course and should not be harvested during floods, as any interference in the natural systems could damage the [[ecosystem]].<ref name=ABCflood>{{cite news|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation News|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-05-09/lake-eyre-is-a-wild-river-system-left-to-run-its-course/11035506|title=Wild Abandon|series=7:30|first= Dominique|last= Schwartz|others=Photography by Brendan Esposito|date= 9 May 2019|accessdate=9 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Yacht club==\nThe Lake Eyre Yacht Club is a dedicated group of sailors who sail on the lake's floods, including recent trips in 1997, 2000, 2001, 2004, 2007 and 2009.<ref>[http://www.lakeeyreyc.com Welcome to the Lake Eyre Yacht Club]. Retrieved 29 March 2012.</ref> A number of {{convert|6|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} [[trailer sailer]]s sailed on Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre in 1975, 1976, and 1984, when the flood depth reached {{convert|3|\u2013|6|m|ft|abbr=on}}. In July 2010 The Yacht Club held its first regatta since 1976<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.lakepedia.com/lake/eyre.html |title=Lake Eyre - 9,690 km2 - Facts, Map, Activities|work=www.lakepedia.com |accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref> and its first on Lake Killamperpunna, a freshwater lake on Cooper Creek. The Cooper had reached Kati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre for the first time since 1990.{{Citation needed|date=April 2016}}\n\nWhen the lake is full, a notable phenomenon is that around midday the surface can often become very flat. The surface then reflects the sky in a way that leaves both the horizon and water surface virtually impossible to see. The commodore of the Lake Eyre Yacht Club has stated that sailing during this time has the appearance of sailing in the sky.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tinson|first1=Sam|title=Dry country|url=http://www.sailsmagazine.com.au/j/index.php/livenews/101-dry-country|accessdate=30 March 2017|work=Sails Magazine|issue=7|date=May 2011|language=en-gb|quote=\u201cOften you get becalmed in the middle of the lake at midday, and the surface is like a mirror, the water and the sky become one. You get a light sea fog and it\u2019s almost like you\u2019re floating in a cloud. It\u2019s a very beautiful thing.\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170331120051/http://www.sailsmagazine.com.au/j/index.php/livenews/101-dry-country|archive-date=31 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Land speed record attempts==\n[[File:EyreCampbellPlaque.JPG|thumb|Campbell plaque at Level Post Bay]]\n\nKati Thanda\u2013Lake Eyre has been a site for various [[land speed record]] attempts on its [[Salt pan (geology)|salt flats]], similar to those found in the [[Bonneville Salt Flats]], especially those by [[Donald Campbell]] with the [[Bluebird-Proteus CN7]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Bluebird and the Dead Lake |author=[[John Pearson (author)]] |url= https://books.google.com/books/about/Bluebird_and_the_Dead_Lake.html?id=VuEBAAAACAAJ&redir_esc=y }}</ref>\n\n==Wildlife==\nPhytoplankton in the lake includes ''[[Nodularia|Nodularia spumigena]]'' and a number of species of ''[[Dunaliella]]''.<ref name=\"lhlrr\"/>\n\n===Birds===\nBirds such as [[Australian pelican|pelicans]] and [[banded stilt]]s are drawn to a filled lake from southern coastal regions of Australia, and from as far afield as Papua New Guinea. During the 1989\u20131990 flood, it was estimated that 200,000 pelicans, 80% of Australia's total population, came to feed & roost at Lake Eyre.<ref name=\"wdrwsg\">{{cite book |title=Why Does the World Stay Green?: Nutrition and Survival of Plant-eaters |last=TCR |first=White |year=2005 |publisher=Csiro Publishing |isbn=0643099816 |page=88 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Zf6pZp20qxEC |accessdate=20 December 2012 }}</ref> Scientists are presently unable to determine how such birds appear able to detect the filling of the lake, even when hundreds or thousands of kilometres away from the basin.<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-01-06/birds-set-to-return-to-lake-eyre-to-breed/7069228?section=sa Birds set to return to Lake Eyre to breed as inland lakes fill with water] ''ABC News'', 6 January 2016. Accessed 6 January 2016.</ref>\n\n==Protected area status==\n\n===Statutory===\nThe extent of the lake is covered by two [[protected area]]s declared by the [[Government of South Australia]] - the [[Kati Thanda-Lake Eyre National Park]] and the [[Elliot Price Conservation Park]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kati Thanda-Lake Eyre National Park Map|url=http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/files/0bf2b3b7-6c15-4f45-a704-a3dc00c3a14a/kati-thanda-lake-eyre-national-park-map.pdf|publisher=Department of Environment, Water and Natural Resources|accessdate=5 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Non-statutory===\n\n====Wetlands====\nLake Eyre is on the list of wetlands of national importance known as [[A Directory of Important Wetlands in Australia]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Eyles|first1=Kathy|title=A Directory of important wetlands in Australia|date=2001|publisher=Environment Australia|isbn=978-0-642-54721-7|page=78|edition=3|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/system/files/resources/18f0bb21-b67c-4e99-a155-cb5255398568/files/directory-ch9.pdf|accessdate=4 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Important bird area====\nLake Eyre has been identified by [[BirdLife International]] as an [[Important Bird Area]] (IBA) known as the Lake Eyre Important Bird Area, because, when flooded, it supports major breeding events of the [[Banded stilt]] and [[Australian pelican]], as well as over 1% of the world populations of [[Red-necked avocet]]s, [[Sharp-tailed sandpiper]]s, [[Red-necked stint]]s, [[Silver gull]]s and [[Caspian tern]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.birdlife.org/datazone/sitefactsheet.php?id=24442 |title= Important Bird Areas factsheet: Lake Eyre |accessdate=5 February 2015 |work= Birdata |publisher=Birdlife International }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{stack|{{portal|Australia}}}}\n* [[Lake Torrens]]\n* [[List of lakes of Australia]]\n* [[Pluvial lake]]\n*[[Eyre (disambiguation)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Commons category|Lake Eyre}}\n\n* {{cite web|format=video|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-05-09/the-re-birth-of-lake-eyre/11099272|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|website=ABC News|series=7:30 Report|title=The re-birth of Lake Eyre|first=Dominique|last=Schwarz|date=10 May 2019}}\n\n*Dr Vincent Kotwicki: ''[http://www.k26.com/eyre/ Floods of Lake Eyre]''  - interesting site with lots of data, including Lake Eyre inflows 1885-2012.\n*[http://www.saltdoco.com/movie-info/synopsis.htm ''Salt''] - documentary film by Murray Fredericks and Michael Angus (synopsis)\n\n*[[NASA Earth Observatory]]: [http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=38994 Lake Eyre Filling Peaks - 21 June 2009]\n\n*[http://www.LakeEyreYC.com Lake Eyre Yacht Club website]\n{{Oceania topic|List of lakes of|title=List of lakes in Oceania}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lake Eyre}}\n[[Category:Ancient lakes]]\n[[Category:Saline lakes of South Australia|Eyre, Lake]]\n[[Category:Endorheic lakes of Australia|Eyre, Lake]]\n[[Category:Lake Eyre basin]]\n[[Category:Far North (South Australia)]]\n[[Category:Extreme points of Australia]]\n[[Category:Lowest points]]\n", "name_user": "Ifsaryan", "label": "safe", "comment": "The natural depth of lake Eyre is 12 m", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake_Eyre"}
